WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.980 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.980 --> 00:00:08.964 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:08.964 --> 00:00:18.946 align:middle line:90%


00:00:18.946 --> 00:00:20.570 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA GARR: If you
believe in destiny,

00:00:20.570 --> 00:00:22.580 align:middle line:84%
you will love the
story of Susan Miller.

00:00:22.580 --> 00:00:26.120 align:middle line:10%
In 1995, Susan was one of the
original internet pioneers

00:00:26.120 --> 00:00:28.170 align:middle line:10%
launching astrologyzone.com.

00:00:28.170 --> 00:00:32.570 align:middle line:10%
And then in 2013, she created
the wildly popular app

00:00:32.570 --> 00:00:33.800 align:middle line:10%
Daily Horoscopes--

00:00:33.800 --> 00:00:36.270 align:middle line:10%
Astrology Zone, which I love.

00:00:36.270 --> 00:00:41.700 align:middle line:84%
And in 2016 alone, the app
generated 22 million sessions.

00:00:41.700 --> 00:00:44.600 align:middle line:84%
But the road has not always
been so smooth for Susan.

00:00:44.600 --> 00:00:46.670 align:middle line:84%
She was born with a
birth defect in her leg,

00:00:46.670 --> 00:00:48.760 align:middle line:90%
which perplexed doctors.

00:00:48.760 --> 00:00:51.740 align:middle line:10%
And it was her mother, a
very talented astrologer

00:00:51.740 --> 00:00:55.190 align:middle line:10%
who taught Susan about
destiny and astrology.

00:00:55.190 --> 00:00:57.620 align:middle line:84%
And this knowledge
helped Susan enormously

00:00:57.620 --> 00:00:59.400 align:middle line:90%
through her healing process.

00:00:59.400 --> 00:01:00.977 align:middle line:10%
Thank you so much
for being here.

00:01:00.977 --> 00:01:02.060 align:middle line:10%
>>SUSAN MILLER: Thank you.

00:01:02.060 --> 00:01:03.770 align:middle line:10%
Thank you for asking me on.

00:01:03.770 --> 00:01:05.140 align:middle line:10%
What an exciting show you have.

00:01:05.140 --> 00:01:05.940 align:middle line:10%
[CHUCKLES]

00:01:05.940 --> 00:01:07.023 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's so wonderful.

00:01:07.023 --> 00:01:09.360 align:middle line:84%
And what you've done, I
mean, it's just incredible.

00:01:09.360 --> 00:01:11.570 align:middle line:90%
So take me back to Little Mom.

00:01:11.570 --> 00:01:13.520 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: Ah, my mother.

00:01:13.520 --> 00:01:15.860 align:middle line:84%
My mother did not want
to teach me astrology.

00:01:15.860 --> 00:01:17.330 align:middle line:90%
I had to keep begging her.

00:01:17.330 --> 00:01:18.260 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Why?

00:01:18.260 --> 00:01:22.670 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: Well, she said a
little knowledge is dangerous.

00:01:22.670 --> 00:01:25.460 align:middle line:90%
And you see it on the internet.

00:01:25.460 --> 00:01:29.112 align:middle line:84%
The internet's great because all
this information is out there,

00:01:29.112 --> 00:01:31.070 align:middle line:84%
but it's not so great
because some people don't

00:01:31.070 --> 00:01:34.700 align:middle line:84%
know how to verify where they're
getting their information from.

00:01:34.700 --> 00:01:35.510 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Now, yeah.

00:01:35.510 --> 00:01:38.120 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: And my mother said,
you have to study 12 years

00:01:38.120 --> 00:01:39.715 align:middle line:90%
or you won't be any good.

00:01:39.715 --> 00:01:41.840 align:middle line:84%
And you're going to start
reading for your friends.

00:01:41.840 --> 00:01:44.600 align:middle line:84%
Well I said, Little Mom,
I don't have any friends.

00:01:44.600 --> 00:01:49.880 align:middle line:84%
I had been in the hospital
at age 14 for 11 months.

00:01:49.880 --> 00:01:52.950 align:middle line:84%
And they had to paralyze
the leg from the knee down.

00:01:52.950 --> 00:01:55.850 align:middle line:84%
They tourniquetted
it so tight that I

00:01:55.850 --> 00:01:58.040 align:middle line:90%
had a drop foot and no feeling.

00:01:58.040 --> 00:01:59.270 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't move it.

00:01:59.270 --> 00:02:00.855 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't do anything.

00:02:00.855 --> 00:02:02.730 align:middle line:84%
And the doctor said, we
didn't have a choice.

00:02:02.730 --> 00:02:04.980 align:middle line:84%
We were either going to lose
you, or the leg, or both.

00:02:04.980 --> 00:02:06.399 align:middle line:90%
So we had to do this.

00:02:06.399 --> 00:02:08.690 align:middle line:84%
And he was the Chief of Staff
of the Hospital for Joint

00:02:08.690 --> 00:02:10.970 align:middle line:90%
Diseases, and I loved him.

00:02:10.970 --> 00:02:14.600 align:middle line:84%
And I just thought,
OK, I mean, I'm here.

00:02:14.600 --> 00:02:15.410 align:middle line:90%
I'm still alive.

00:02:15.410 --> 00:02:16.160 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's a big decision.

00:02:16.160 --> 00:02:18.326 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: I knew it was
going to be a big operation.

00:02:18.326 --> 00:02:20.480 align:middle line:90%
No one else did, including him.

00:02:20.480 --> 00:02:23.600 align:middle line:84%
But they found out my veins
were made of tissue paper

00:02:23.600 --> 00:02:25.790 align:middle line:84%
and would varnish
under pressure.

00:02:25.790 --> 00:02:29.450 align:middle line:84%
Pressure could be being
happy for Santa Claus coming,

00:02:29.450 --> 00:02:34.270 align:middle line:84%
or being happy for my
birthday, or having surgery

00:02:34.270 --> 00:02:35.960 align:middle line:90%
is pressure on the body.

00:02:35.960 --> 00:02:38.930 align:middle line:84%
And he faced one of the
worst operations of his life.

00:02:38.930 --> 00:02:42.050 align:middle line:84%
And he was an orthopedic
surgeon, not a vascular cardio

00:02:42.050 --> 00:02:43.230 align:middle line:90%
man.

00:02:43.230 --> 00:02:44.850 align:middle line:90%
And yet, he was brilliant.

00:02:44.850 --> 00:02:48.470 align:middle line:84%
He went to Oxford, and he
was a Fulbright scholar,

00:02:48.470 --> 00:02:50.900 align:middle line:84%
and, I mean, he just
had all those degrees.

00:02:50.900 --> 00:02:52.010 align:middle line:90%
He did figure it out.

00:02:52.010 --> 00:02:55.550 align:middle line:84%
He said, look, Susie, we
have to first straighten out

00:02:55.550 --> 00:02:57.300 align:middle line:84%
the circulatory
system, but then you're

00:02:57.300 --> 00:03:01.480 align:middle line:84%
going to go into three
years of therapy.

00:03:01.480 --> 00:03:04.939 align:middle line:84%
Every day, six hours a
day, five days a week.

00:03:04.939 --> 00:03:05.855 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: As a teenager.

00:03:05.855 --> 00:03:06.813 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: You're young.

00:03:06.813 --> 00:03:08.330 align:middle line:90%
We're going to bring it back.

00:03:08.330 --> 00:03:09.230 align:middle line:90%
And I walked.

00:03:09.230 --> 00:03:10.470 align:middle line:90%
And I don't have crutches.

00:03:10.470 --> 00:03:13.700 align:middle line:84%
And I always called my
crutches my chopsticks.

00:03:13.700 --> 00:03:16.470 align:middle line:90%
And I had a brace up to here.

00:03:16.470 --> 00:03:18.392 align:middle line:84%
And I just wanted to
know if all that I

00:03:18.392 --> 00:03:19.850 align:middle line:84%
was going to go
through-- because I

00:03:19.850 --> 00:03:20.975 align:middle line:90%
had to give up high school.

00:03:20.975 --> 00:03:22.970 align:middle line:10%
I went from junior
high to college--

00:03:22.970 --> 00:03:25.010 align:middle line:10%
if that was going to work.

00:03:25.010 --> 00:03:28.377 align:middle line:84%
If all that effort had
a rainbow at the end.

00:03:28.377 --> 00:03:29.710 align:middle line:90%
And my mother wouldn't teach me.

00:03:29.710 --> 00:03:31.730 align:middle line:90%
She kept saying, no, no, no.

00:03:31.730 --> 00:03:34.070 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But she was reading
you the whole time, right?

00:03:34.070 --> 00:03:36.830 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: Yes And she had books.

00:03:36.830 --> 00:03:38.570 align:middle line:84%
So my sister would
take the books

00:03:38.570 --> 00:03:41.120 align:middle line:84%
off the shelf, put
them in my room

00:03:41.120 --> 00:03:43.880 align:middle line:90%
under the dust ruffle of my bed.

00:03:43.880 --> 00:03:46.280 align:middle line:84%
And then I would read them,
and Jenna would come home,

00:03:46.280 --> 00:03:47.730 align:middle line:90%
and put them back on the shelf.

00:03:47.730 --> 00:03:48.530 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:03:48.530 --> 00:03:51.560 align:middle line:84%
And my mother didn't know I
was studying all her textbooks.

00:03:51.560 --> 00:03:54.890 align:middle line:84%
And finally, one day she
walked into the living room.

00:03:54.890 --> 00:03:58.190 align:middle line:84%
I was writing a paper
on my typewriter.

00:03:58.190 --> 00:04:02.390 align:middle line:84%
And she said, did you write
to "Horoscope" magazine.

00:04:02.390 --> 00:04:04.460 align:middle line:84%
I thought, how
does she know that?

00:04:04.460 --> 00:04:08.500 align:middle line:84%
I said, yes, but they
never answered me.

00:04:08.500 --> 00:04:12.080 align:middle line:84%
She pulled out the envelope,
the latest issue and she said,

00:04:12.080 --> 00:04:13.640 align:middle line:90%
you're in this issue, Susan.

00:04:13.640 --> 00:04:14.510 align:middle line:90%
It has to be you.

00:04:14.510 --> 00:04:17.220 align:middle line:84%
It's your birthday, your time
of birth, your city of birth,

00:04:17.220 --> 00:04:18.260 align:middle line:90%
your problem.

00:04:18.260 --> 00:04:19.600 align:middle line:90%
This is you, isn't it?

00:04:19.600 --> 00:04:21.230 align:middle line:90%
I'm like, yes.

00:04:21.230 --> 00:04:22.916 align:middle line:84%
Well, you wouldn't
teach me astrology,

00:04:22.916 --> 00:04:25.040 align:middle line:84%
so I needed a second opinion,
because you're always

00:04:25.040 --> 00:04:26.840 align:middle line:90%
so optimistic, Little Mom.

00:04:26.840 --> 00:04:28.730 align:middle line:90%
I wanted a second opinion.

00:04:28.730 --> 00:04:31.160 align:middle line:84%
So I said, what did the lady
say, the editor in chief?

00:04:31.160 --> 00:04:34.140 align:middle line:84%
And she said, well,
let's read it together.

00:04:34.140 --> 00:04:37.280 align:middle line:84%
And when you're asking a
question of an astrologer,

00:04:37.280 --> 00:04:39.110 align:middle line:90%
there's no definite yes or no.

00:04:39.110 --> 00:04:41.930 align:middle line:84%
You're putting pieces
of a puzzle together.

00:04:41.930 --> 00:04:43.310 align:middle line:90%
Great family support.

00:04:43.310 --> 00:04:45.140 align:middle line:90%
Good attitude of the patient.

00:04:45.140 --> 00:04:46.640 align:middle line:90%
Lives in a big city.

00:04:46.640 --> 00:04:49.550 align:middle line:90%
Access to great facilities.

00:04:49.550 --> 00:04:52.550 align:middle line:84%
Jupiter in the right
place to help her recover.

00:04:52.550 --> 00:04:53.940 align:middle line:90%
All kinds of things like that.

00:04:53.940 --> 00:04:55.580 align:middle line:84%
And they said at
the end, we think

00:04:55.580 --> 00:04:57.770 align:middle line:90%
you're going to walk again.

00:04:57.770 --> 00:05:00.930 align:middle line:84%
And so I said, Little Mom, what
do those astrological terms

00:05:00.930 --> 00:05:01.730 align:middle line:90%
mean?

00:05:01.730 --> 00:05:03.500 align:middle line:90%
You have to teach me.

00:05:03.500 --> 00:05:05.840 align:middle line:84%
She said, but you
already have your answer.

00:05:05.840 --> 00:05:07.580 align:middle line:84%
And I just looked
at her and I smiled.

00:05:07.580 --> 00:05:09.320 align:middle line:84%
And she said, oh
no, you're going

00:05:09.320 --> 00:05:10.750 align:middle line:90%
to check the editor in chief.

00:05:10.750 --> 00:05:11.960 align:middle line:90%
And I'm like, of course.

00:05:11.960 --> 00:05:12.760 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: [LAUGHS]

00:05:12.760 --> 00:05:15.009 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: She said, you're
never going to stop asking.

00:05:15.009 --> 00:05:15.990 align:middle line:90%
I said, never.

00:05:15.990 --> 00:05:19.930 align:middle line:10%
12 years, you're not to read
one chart outside the family.

00:05:19.930 --> 00:05:21.520 align:middle line:84%
Now, I had a lot of
Italian relatives.

00:05:21.520 --> 00:05:22.645 align:middle line:90%
My mother was from German--

00:05:22.645 --> 00:05:24.269 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Oh, so you
had a lot of family.

00:05:24.269 --> 00:05:26.110 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: And German
has to be-- you know.

00:05:26.110 --> 00:05:28.170 align:middle line:84%
But all my aunts and
uncles lived upstairs.

00:05:28.170 --> 00:05:29.170 align:middle line:90%
I was like, OK, do me.

00:05:29.170 --> 00:05:30.030 align:middle line:90%
Do me.

00:05:30.030 --> 00:05:31.690 align:middle line:90%
And my mother would be there.

00:05:31.690 --> 00:05:34.261 align:middle line:84%
And she said, I will tell
you when you're ready.

00:05:34.261 --> 00:05:36.760 align:middle line:84%
But it's going to take 12 years
because you have to build up

00:05:36.760 --> 00:05:38.710 align:middle line:84%
all these synapses
in your brain,

00:05:38.710 --> 00:05:43.420 align:middle line:84%
because you have to juggle eight
planets plus the sun and moon,

00:05:43.420 --> 00:05:46.810 align:middle line:84%
and then the transiting
ones, so you double that.

00:05:46.810 --> 00:05:49.270 align:middle line:90%
And there's a lot of math.

00:05:49.270 --> 00:05:51.080 align:middle line:90%
And I love geometry.

00:05:51.080 --> 00:05:52.510 align:middle line:90%
So I'm doing that all day long.

00:05:52.510 --> 00:05:53.740 align:middle line:90%
And people say I'm psychic.

00:05:53.740 --> 00:05:55.160 align:middle line:90%
I'm not at all.

00:05:55.160 --> 00:05:56.370 align:middle line:90%
God has a plan for us.

00:05:56.370 --> 00:05:57.170 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Uh-huh.

00:05:57.170 --> 00:05:57.410 align:middle line:90%
Obviously.

00:05:57.410 --> 00:05:58.210 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:05:58.210 --> 00:06:00.640 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: We're systematically
rewarded and challenged

00:06:00.640 --> 00:06:03.610 align:middle line:84%
systematically to teach
us certain things.

00:06:03.610 --> 00:06:06.570 align:middle line:84%
But nobody, not
one astrologer ever

00:06:06.570 --> 00:06:08.817 align:middle line:84%
met when they're
little says, I want

00:06:08.817 --> 00:06:10.150 align:middle line:90%
to grow up and be an astrologer.

00:06:10.150 --> 00:06:11.560 align:middle line:90%
I certainly didn't want to.

00:06:11.560 --> 00:06:13.610 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to be accepted.

00:06:13.610 --> 00:06:15.610 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to be in a normal job.

00:06:15.610 --> 00:06:18.490 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yes, yes, but look at
the journey you went through,

00:06:18.490 --> 00:06:20.380 align:middle line:90%
and what an inspiration.

00:06:20.380 --> 00:06:22.540 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: Well, it was
"Time Life" that came to me

00:06:22.540 --> 00:06:27.760 align:middle line:84%
and said, write a column
for our website in 1995.

00:06:27.760 --> 00:06:29.830 align:middle line:84%
I remember that
taxi ride downtown.

00:06:29.830 --> 00:06:31.750 align:middle line:84%
I knew it was going
to change my life,

00:06:31.750 --> 00:06:33.724 align:middle line:90%
because when I was little--

00:06:33.724 --> 00:06:35.140 align:middle line:84%
you're not going
to believe this--

00:06:35.140 --> 00:06:38.740 align:middle line:84%
I sit, nine years old,
mommy, read my chart.

00:06:38.740 --> 00:06:41.110 align:middle line:84%
And she said, well,
you're going to write.

00:06:41.110 --> 00:06:41.980 align:middle line:90%
I said, write?

00:06:41.980 --> 00:06:43.921 align:middle line:84%
No one in our family
write for a living.

00:06:43.921 --> 00:06:46.420 align:middle line:84%
You're going to write and I'm
going to work on your grammar.

00:06:46.420 --> 00:06:48.060 align:middle line:84%
I'm not sure what
you're writing about.

00:06:48.060 --> 00:06:48.860 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:06:48.860 --> 00:06:51.080 align:middle line:84%
Isn't that like what
a mom would say?

00:06:51.080 --> 00:06:54.550 align:middle line:84%
And then she said, when you
get to the end of your 30s,

00:06:54.550 --> 00:06:57.790 align:middle line:84%
some newly invented
form of communication--

00:06:57.790 --> 00:07:00.490 align:middle line:84%
so new we don't know
the name of it yet--

00:07:00.490 --> 00:07:02.650 align:middle line:84%
it will change the
way you work and be

00:07:02.650 --> 00:07:06.400 align:middle line:84%
the channel in which you make
your ultimate contribution

00:07:06.400 --> 00:07:08.090 align:middle line:90%
to the world.

00:07:08.090 --> 00:07:11.065 align:middle line:84%
I was thunderstruck,
because as little as five,

00:07:11.065 --> 00:07:12.790 align:middle line:90%
I remember playing on--

00:07:12.790 --> 00:07:13.990 align:middle line:90%
I might have been six--

00:07:13.990 --> 00:07:16.480 align:middle line:84%
playing blocks while my
sister slept in the crib,

00:07:16.480 --> 00:07:18.580 align:middle line:84%
because we're a
four-year difference.

00:07:18.580 --> 00:07:21.430 align:middle line:84%
And my mother's big blue eyes
coming close to me saying,

00:07:21.430 --> 00:07:24.610 align:middle line:84%
did you ever wonder why
you were born, Susan?

00:07:24.610 --> 00:07:25.410 align:middle line:90%
No, mommy.

00:07:25.410 --> 00:07:26.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: [LAUGHS]

00:07:26.050 --> 00:07:28.008 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: Well, we all
need to think about that

00:07:28.008 --> 00:07:29.510 align:middle line:84%
and we all need
to find an answer.

00:07:29.510 --> 00:07:32.120 align:middle line:84%
So my mother was
deeply philosophical.

00:07:32.120 --> 00:07:35.464 align:middle line:84%
So now I'm nine and she's
giving me a clue of where--

00:07:35.464 --> 00:07:36.880 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you
remember all this.

00:07:36.880 --> 00:07:38.255 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: --that's
going to-- oh,

00:07:38.255 --> 00:07:40.390 align:middle line:90%
it was like a choir of angels.

00:07:40.390 --> 00:07:43.840 align:middle line:84%
I have Aquarius on the
top of the mid-heaven,

00:07:43.840 --> 00:07:46.090 align:middle line:90%
where 12 is on the clock.

00:07:46.090 --> 00:07:50.360 align:middle line:84%
And she said, Aquarius
is what's invented next.

00:07:50.360 --> 00:07:51.160 align:middle line:90%
I drove her crazy.

00:07:51.160 --> 00:07:51.730 align:middle line:90%
What could it be?

00:07:51.730 --> 00:07:52.450 align:middle line:90%
How do you know?

00:07:52.450 --> 00:07:53.908 align:middle line:84%
You're looking at
a piece of paper.

00:07:53.908 --> 00:07:55.360 align:middle line:90%
How do you know?

00:07:55.360 --> 00:07:59.990 align:middle line:84%
She said, somehow
connected with electricity.

00:07:59.990 --> 00:08:02.500 align:middle line:84%
So this is getting
even more mysterious.

00:08:02.500 --> 00:08:04.450 align:middle line:90%
And you know how kids are.

00:08:04.450 --> 00:08:05.391 align:middle line:90%
They don't let up.

00:08:05.391 --> 00:08:06.640 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: They don't stop, yeah.

00:08:06.640 --> 00:08:09.160 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: So that
week, I kept it up.

00:08:09.160 --> 00:08:14.150 align:middle line:84%
She said, look,
Aquarius is an air sign.

00:08:14.150 --> 00:08:15.620 align:middle line:90%
It's the little zigzags.

00:08:15.620 --> 00:08:17.210 align:middle line:90%
That's air.

00:08:17.210 --> 00:08:19.040 align:middle line:84%
There's little
lines or dots that

00:08:19.040 --> 00:08:21.980 align:middle line:84%
go through the air that's
invisible that's somehow

00:08:21.980 --> 00:08:23.399 align:middle line:90%
associated with your writing.

00:08:23.399 --> 00:08:25.190 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: She didn't know
about the internet.

00:08:25.190 --> 00:08:25.800 align:middle line:90%
There was no clue.

00:08:25.800 --> 00:08:28.049 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: It wasn't even in
the paper or anything yet.

00:08:28.049 --> 00:08:28.850 align:middle line:90%
I was so little.

00:08:28.850 --> 00:08:29.510 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's amazing.

00:08:29.510 --> 00:08:29.720 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: I know.

00:08:29.720 --> 00:08:31.810 align:middle line:84%
I was born in little
house on the prairie time.

00:08:31.810 --> 00:08:32.110 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:08:32.110 --> 00:08:34.280 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So then how did
you get to starting it?

00:08:34.280 --> 00:08:35.900 align:middle line:84%
I mean, how did it
all come together?

00:08:35.900 --> 00:08:37.309 align:middle line:90%
Well, you launched that in 1989.

00:08:37.309 --> 00:08:40.580 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: Well, I was an agent
for commercial photographers.

00:08:40.580 --> 00:08:43.590 align:middle line:84%
And I love dealing
with creative people.

00:08:43.590 --> 00:08:45.680 align:middle line:84%
It's my favorite thing
in the whole world.

00:08:45.680 --> 00:08:50.220 align:middle line:84%
And I had a photographer who
I had looked at 100 portfolios

00:08:50.220 --> 00:08:51.230 align:middle line:90%
and I picked him.

00:08:51.230 --> 00:08:54.200 align:middle line:84%
He did splashes, spills,
and pours so gracefully.

00:08:54.200 --> 00:08:56.270 align:middle line:84%
And he never said, we'll
fix it in the system.

00:08:56.270 --> 00:08:58.860 align:middle line:90%
He would fix it on film.

00:08:58.860 --> 00:09:01.640 align:middle line:84%
And I took the two creative
directors to lunch.

00:09:01.640 --> 00:09:03.950 align:middle line:84%
They were from
Saatchi & Saatchi.

00:09:03.950 --> 00:09:06.860 align:middle line:84%
Scott said to me, my
wife would love you.

00:09:06.860 --> 00:09:08.120 align:middle line:90%
I said, I would love her.

00:09:08.120 --> 00:09:09.330 align:middle line:90%
What does she do?

00:09:09.330 --> 00:09:12.920 align:middle line:84%
And he said, she's creative
director of Warner Books.

00:09:12.920 --> 00:09:15.620 align:middle line:84%
I'd like you to go up
there and say hello to her.

00:09:15.620 --> 00:09:18.800 align:middle line:84%
Well, those were the days where
you still did call on people.

00:09:18.800 --> 00:09:21.375 align:middle line:84%
Not like now, that everything's
become so impersonal.

00:09:21.375 --> 00:09:22.175 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Text, yeah.

00:09:22.175 --> 00:09:24.424 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: I did go up there
and she'd give me galleys.

00:09:24.424 --> 00:09:25.270 align:middle line:90%
She'd give me books.

00:09:25.270 --> 00:09:26.910 align:middle line:90%
She'd give me things.

00:09:26.910 --> 00:09:29.060 align:middle line:90%
And I would read her chart.

00:09:29.060 --> 00:09:31.250 align:middle line:90%
We would have fun.

00:09:31.250 --> 00:09:34.700 align:middle line:84%
And when I was an agent, you'd
go from agency to agency,

00:09:34.700 --> 00:09:36.526 align:middle line:84%
but sometimes you had
an hour in between.

00:09:36.526 --> 00:09:38.150 align:middle line:84%
So I'd run up to the
Time Life building

00:09:38.150 --> 00:09:41.690 align:middle line:90%
on 6th Avenue and 50th street.

00:09:41.690 --> 00:09:45.680 align:middle line:84%
And one day she said, I
have a feeling about you.

00:09:45.680 --> 00:09:47.420 align:middle line:90%
Someday, I'll get you a book.

00:09:47.420 --> 00:09:48.260 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow, nice.

00:09:48.260 --> 00:09:50.750 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: Now, it's
very hard for a person

00:09:50.750 --> 00:09:55.630 align:middle line:84%
to see you in another
role usually in society.

00:09:55.630 --> 00:09:57.800 align:middle line:90%
Five years go by, nothing.

00:09:57.800 --> 00:09:59.330 align:middle line:90%
And I never mentioned it again.

00:09:59.330 --> 00:10:01.880 align:middle line:84%
I thought it was just
sweet for her to say that.

00:10:01.880 --> 00:10:05.810 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes when I walk
along the sidewalk, I'd say,

00:10:05.810 --> 00:10:07.400 align:middle line:84%
I wonder what would
have happened if I

00:10:07.400 --> 00:10:09.110 align:middle line:90%
would have gotten that book.

00:10:09.110 --> 00:10:11.190 align:middle line:90%
Would my life have changed?

00:10:11.190 --> 00:10:13.070 align:middle line:90%
And one day she calls me.

00:10:13.070 --> 00:10:16.980 align:middle line:84%
It's 1994 and she says, I
have good news and bad news.

00:10:16.980 --> 00:10:18.680 align:middle line:90%
I said, give me the good news.

00:10:18.680 --> 00:10:19.830 align:middle line:90%
I have your book.

00:10:19.830 --> 00:10:21.290 align:middle line:10%
I said, you meant it?

00:10:21.290 --> 00:10:23.020 align:middle line:10%
It's just a little book.

00:10:23.020 --> 00:10:25.460 align:middle line:84%
The bad news is you've got
to write it really quickly.

00:10:25.460 --> 00:10:27.560 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't have
the website yet.

00:10:27.560 --> 00:10:29.450 align:middle line:90%
So I said sure.

00:10:29.450 --> 00:10:31.100 align:middle line:84%
It's sold out and
then she said, I'm

00:10:31.100 --> 00:10:32.965 align:middle line:90%
sending you to the webmaster.

00:10:32.965 --> 00:10:34.340 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Oh, that's
what happened.

00:10:34.340 --> 00:10:36.500 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: And I said,
what do they want?

00:10:36.500 --> 00:10:38.990 align:middle line:90%
And she said, they don't know.

00:10:38.990 --> 00:10:41.270 align:middle line:90%
And I'm glad she said that.

00:10:41.270 --> 00:10:43.740 align:middle line:84%
And you really should
disagree with management

00:10:43.740 --> 00:10:45.560 align:middle line:84%
if you think their
direction is wrong.

00:10:45.560 --> 00:10:50.074 align:middle line:84%
If your listeners have anything
to take away, it's that.

00:10:50.074 --> 00:10:51.740 align:middle line:84%
And I said to them,
what would you like?

00:10:51.740 --> 00:10:53.930 align:middle line:84%
And they said something
short for women every day.

00:10:53.930 --> 00:10:56.150 align:middle line:84%
I said, no, this
isn't a girl thing.

00:10:56.150 --> 00:10:58.430 align:middle line:90%
Men love astrology.

00:10:58.430 --> 00:11:01.040 align:middle line:84%
And I will write
in a detailed way.

00:11:01.040 --> 00:11:03.350 align:middle line:90%
We must write long--

00:11:03.350 --> 00:11:06.950 align:middle line:84%
not short-- long for men
and women once a month.

00:11:06.950 --> 00:11:09.995 align:middle line:84%
They said, Susan, you're flying
in the face of web wisdom.

00:11:09.995 --> 00:11:12.590 align:middle line:84%
It's supposed to be short,
no more than 500 words.

00:11:12.590 --> 00:11:14.990 align:middle line:84%
I said, yeah, that's
good for other people,

00:11:14.990 --> 00:11:17.460 align:middle line:84%
but when it's about
the reader, then

00:11:17.460 --> 00:11:19.560 align:middle line:84%
you should give them
chock full of information.

00:11:19.560 --> 00:11:20.360 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's true.

00:11:20.360 --> 00:11:22.312 align:middle line:90%
I read every single word.

00:11:22.312 --> 00:11:24.020 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: And I even
give them a summary.

00:11:24.020 --> 00:11:24.890 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And I took notes.

00:11:24.890 --> 00:11:25.690 align:middle line:90%
Yes, exactly.

00:11:25.690 --> 00:11:26.510 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:11:26.510 --> 00:11:27.620 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: And
summaries sometimes

00:11:27.620 --> 00:11:28.911 align:middle line:90%
have things that are different.

00:11:28.911 --> 00:11:30.900 align:middle line:84%
Well, I write my summary
three months ahead.

00:11:30.900 --> 00:11:32.210 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Oh, they are
different, aren't they?

00:11:32.210 --> 00:11:33.010 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: Yeah.

00:11:33.010 --> 00:11:34.700 align:middle line:84%
So sometimes, I say
to myself, oh, I

00:11:34.700 --> 00:11:36.470 align:middle line:84%
didn't talk about
Scorpio's apartment,

00:11:36.470 --> 00:11:37.710 align:middle line:90%
but I have nowhere to put it.

00:11:37.710 --> 00:11:40.514 align:middle line:84%
So I'll just leave it down here
as little bits of chocolate.

00:11:40.514 --> 00:11:42.680 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Because I take notes
throughout the summary,

00:11:42.680 --> 00:11:44.471 align:middle line:84%
and then you have it
summarized, and then I

00:11:44.471 --> 00:11:45.640 align:middle line:90%
put them into my calendar.

00:11:45.640 --> 00:11:47.000 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: That's so good.

00:11:47.000 --> 00:11:49.070 align:middle line:90%
Well, I sell a calendar.

00:11:49.070 --> 00:11:52.100 align:middle line:84%
And you can just see
that certain days are

00:11:52.100 --> 00:11:53.267 align:middle line:90%
coming that are really good.

00:11:53.267 --> 00:11:54.683 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Let me ask
you a question.

00:11:54.683 --> 00:11:55.910 align:middle line:90%
You've thought of it all.

00:11:55.910 --> 00:11:58.080 align:middle line:84%
But do you do this
based on astrology?

00:11:58.080 --> 00:11:58.880 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: Mhm.

00:11:58.880 --> 00:12:00.796 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You do everything
based on the charts?

00:12:00.796 --> 00:12:03.560 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: Anything I say,
you can look up in a book.

00:12:03.560 --> 00:12:05.460 align:middle line:90%
That's very important to me.

00:12:05.460 --> 00:12:09.260 align:middle line:84%
And I do give the provenance
of everything I say.

00:12:09.260 --> 00:12:14.810 align:middle line:84%
I feel almost like a lawyer has
to persuade you to believe me.

00:12:14.810 --> 00:12:16.340 align:middle line:90%
This is really good.

00:12:16.340 --> 00:12:19.220 align:middle line:90%
It's not coming back until 2026.

00:12:19.220 --> 00:12:21.780 align:middle line:90%
Please take this seriously.

00:12:21.780 --> 00:12:26.360 align:middle line:84%
You'll see how I really try to
present my case to the reader,

00:12:26.360 --> 00:12:29.405 align:middle line:84%
because in my mind, the
reader's saying, so what?

00:12:29.405 --> 00:12:30.530 align:middle line:90%
Why should I listen to you?

00:12:30.530 --> 00:12:30.930 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:12:30.930 --> 00:12:31.800 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:12:31.800 --> 00:12:32.600 align:middle line:90%
So you know that.

00:12:32.600 --> 00:12:33.920 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: I'll tell you why.

00:12:33.920 --> 00:12:34.985 align:middle line:90%
And you don't have to.

00:12:34.985 --> 00:12:36.950 align:middle line:90%
You have free will.

00:12:36.950 --> 00:12:39.380 align:middle line:84%
But if you do, you're
going to do really well.

00:12:39.380 --> 00:12:41.510 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, you are
an accredited astrologer

00:12:41.510 --> 00:12:44.880 align:middle line:84%
by the International Society
of Astrological Research, which

00:12:44.880 --> 00:12:45.680 align:middle line:90%
is amazing.

00:12:45.680 --> 00:12:49.130 align:middle line:84%
You went and did that
before or after college?

00:12:49.130 --> 00:12:50.630 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: They test,
you that's all.

00:12:50.630 --> 00:12:52.430 align:middle line:90%
And they read your writing.

00:12:52.430 --> 00:12:53.315 align:middle line:90%
And it's like that.

00:12:53.315 --> 00:12:53.810 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Fantastic.

00:12:53.810 --> 00:12:54.610 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:12:54.610 --> 00:12:56.600 align:middle line:84%
But your idea into
the wisdom, so--

00:12:56.600 --> 00:12:57.995 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: That was later.

00:12:57.995 --> 00:13:02.030 align:middle line:84%
I didn't really tell people
I knew astrology for years.

00:13:02.030 --> 00:13:02.980 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:13:02.980 --> 00:13:05.150 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: Did you know
before my mother died--

00:13:05.150 --> 00:13:06.380 align:middle line:84%
I would always come
over to her house.

00:13:06.380 --> 00:13:07.754 align:middle line:84%
She was right in
the neighborhood

00:13:07.754 --> 00:13:09.630 align:middle line:90%
and I didn't have to call.

00:13:09.630 --> 00:13:11.430 align:middle line:90%
She was always happy to see me.

00:13:11.430 --> 00:13:13.340 align:middle line:84%
So she's sitting in
her little chair,

00:13:13.340 --> 00:13:14.965 align:middle line:84%
like, Little Mom,
what are you reading?

00:13:14.965 --> 00:13:16.589 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Why do you
call her Little Mom?

00:13:16.589 --> 00:13:18.030 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: Well, she was so tiny.

00:13:18.030 --> 00:13:20.040 align:middle line:90%
She was teeny weeny.

00:13:20.040 --> 00:13:22.550 align:middle line:90%
She's 4 foot 11.

00:13:22.550 --> 00:13:24.960 align:middle line:84%
The doctor said, how tall
are you Mrs. [INAUDIBLE]??

00:13:24.960 --> 00:13:27.120 align:middle line:90%
She said, I'm 5 foot 7.

00:13:27.120 --> 00:13:28.020 align:middle line:90%
He calls me up.

00:13:28.020 --> 00:13:29.490 align:middle line:90%
Was she ever 5 foot 7?

00:13:29.490 --> 00:13:30.630 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:13:30.630 --> 00:13:32.130 align:middle line:84%
She just thinks of
herself that way.

00:13:32.130 --> 00:13:32.640 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That makes sense.

00:13:32.640 --> 00:13:33.598 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: Do not panic.

00:13:33.598 --> 00:13:34.920 align:middle line:90%
She was always little.

00:13:34.920 --> 00:13:39.810 align:middle line:84%
So I think at her tallest
stage, she was 5'' 1'.

00:13:39.810 --> 00:13:41.910 align:middle line:84%
But you shrink a
little bit as you get.

00:13:41.910 --> 00:13:42.840 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:13:42.840 --> 00:13:44.580 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: But she
was sitting, reading,

00:13:44.580 --> 00:13:47.910 align:middle line:84%
and I said, what
are you reading?

00:13:47.910 --> 00:13:49.020 align:middle line:90%
And I go behind her.

00:13:49.020 --> 00:13:51.980 align:middle line:84%
You're reading "Gemini's
Astrology Zone."

00:13:51.980 --> 00:13:54.850 align:middle line:84%
But mom, you know
what's going to happen.

00:13:54.850 --> 00:13:55.980 align:middle line:90%
Why are you reading that?

00:13:55.980 --> 00:13:58.710 align:middle line:84%
And wait a minute, you
don't even have a computer.

00:13:58.710 --> 00:14:01.660 align:middle line:84%
She said, your sister prints
it out for me every month.

00:14:01.660 --> 00:14:02.650 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: [LAUGHS]

00:14:02.650 --> 00:14:04.358 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: And I said,
why do you read it?

00:14:04.358 --> 00:14:06.360 align:middle line:84%
She said, I want to
see what you're saying.

00:14:06.360 --> 00:14:07.392 align:middle line:90%
I said, oh.

00:14:07.392 --> 00:14:08.350 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Is it any good?

00:14:08.350 --> 00:14:10.050 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: How am I doing?

00:14:10.050 --> 00:14:12.660 align:middle line:84%
And she goes like this
with a twinkle in her eyes.

00:14:12.660 --> 00:14:13.600 align:middle line:90%
You can continue.

00:14:13.600 --> 00:14:14.400 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Nice.

00:14:14.400 --> 00:14:14.630 align:middle line:90%
Validation

00:14:14.630 --> 00:14:15.430 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: Yeah.

00:14:15.430 --> 00:14:17.730 align:middle line:90%
And I gave her such a big kiss.

00:14:17.730 --> 00:14:22.890 align:middle line:84%
No-- she-- tone,
attitude, spirit

00:14:22.890 --> 00:14:24.660 align:middle line:84%
in the way you
convey information

00:14:24.660 --> 00:14:27.195 align:middle line:90%
was just as important to her.

00:14:27.195 --> 00:14:28.570 align:middle line:90%
And it is to me, too.

00:14:28.570 --> 00:14:30.240 align:middle line:90%
It's just innate.

00:14:30.240 --> 00:14:31.350 align:middle line:90%
But I love that about her.

00:14:31.350 --> 00:14:34.290 align:middle line:84%
Once a prisoner wrote
to me from jail.

00:14:34.290 --> 00:14:37.285 align:middle line:84%
When I had just started,
he wrote to the publisher

00:14:37.285 --> 00:14:38.160 align:middle line:90%
and I get the letter.

00:14:38.160 --> 00:14:41.610 align:middle line:84%
And I said, a person
in jail wrote to me.

00:14:41.610 --> 00:14:43.200 align:middle line:84%
She said, I hope
you're answering it.

00:14:43.200 --> 00:14:44.940 align:middle line:90%
I said, I am.

00:14:44.940 --> 00:14:48.210 align:middle line:84%
And her exact words was,
even that poor devil

00:14:48.210 --> 00:14:51.020 align:middle line:90%
needs inspiration and hope.

00:14:51.020 --> 00:14:52.230 align:middle line:90%
And I loved her for that.

00:14:52.230 --> 00:14:52.740 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Is that why you do it?

00:14:52.740 --> 00:14:55.530 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: So I wrote the answer
and I gave it back to my editor

00:14:55.530 --> 00:14:58.530 align:middle line:84%
so I wouldn't have my
own address on there.

00:14:58.530 --> 00:15:00.600 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You do go
into great detail.

00:15:00.600 --> 00:15:03.210 align:middle line:84%
What is the difference,
I've always wondered about,

00:15:03.210 --> 00:15:04.720 align:middle line:84%
the Vedic astrology
and what you do?

00:15:04.720 --> 00:15:06.670 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: Oh, Vedic
is very different.

00:15:06.670 --> 00:15:08.850 align:middle line:90%
It comes from India.

00:15:08.850 --> 00:15:14.060 align:middle line:84%
Now, to get a teeny bit
technical but not very,

00:15:14.060 --> 00:15:17.120 align:middle line:84%
the Earth rotates
three different ways,

00:15:17.120 --> 00:15:19.040 align:middle line:90%
but most people think only two.

00:15:19.040 --> 00:15:22.250 align:middle line:84%
Day and night, summer,
fall, winter, spring.

00:15:22.250 --> 00:15:24.020 align:middle line:84%
But there's another
way it rotates,

00:15:24.020 --> 00:15:25.490 align:middle line:90%
and I have to explain that.

00:15:25.490 --> 00:15:27.950 align:middle line:84%
Imagine our solar system
on a dinner plate.

00:15:27.950 --> 00:15:31.580 align:middle line:84%
And it's spinning, and spinning,
and spinning through space.

00:15:31.580 --> 00:15:34.430 align:middle line:84%
The whole solar system
on this dinner plate.

00:15:34.430 --> 00:15:37.410 align:middle line:84%
And it goes through
a retrograde motion.

00:15:37.410 --> 00:15:38.930 align:middle line:84%
So most of us were
born in the age

00:15:38.930 --> 00:15:42.720 align:middle line:84%
of Pisces, the age of
cathedrals and religion.

00:15:42.720 --> 00:15:46.910 align:middle line:84%
Now it has moved retrograde
into the Age of Aquarius.

00:15:46.910 --> 00:15:52.610 align:middle line:84%
Each age is 2,000,
2,200 years long.

00:15:52.610 --> 00:15:56.900 align:middle line:84%
It takes 26,000 years to go
all the way around and make

00:15:56.900 --> 00:15:59.150 align:middle line:90%
a full rotation.

00:15:59.150 --> 00:16:01.910 align:middle line:84%
We are in the Age
of Aquarius now.

00:16:01.910 --> 00:16:06.140 align:middle line:84%
The Vedics know and
we know that there's

00:16:06.140 --> 00:16:10.550 align:middle line:84%
precession of the equinox
where the constellations move

00:16:10.550 --> 00:16:14.030 align:middle line:90%
one degree every 72 years.

00:16:14.030 --> 00:16:18.710 align:middle line:84%
And they make the correction
in their form of astrology.

00:16:18.710 --> 00:16:23.420 align:middle line:84%
Western astrology does
not make the correction,

00:16:23.420 --> 00:16:26.120 align:middle line:84%
because it's called
sidereal astrology.

00:16:26.120 --> 00:16:27.540 align:middle line:90%
It's right in my computer.

00:16:27.540 --> 00:16:31.387 align:middle line:84%
I could tell you what the
Vedic method would be for you.

00:16:31.387 --> 00:16:33.095 align:middle line:84%
But we have found with
Western astrology,

00:16:33.095 --> 00:16:35.680 align:middle line:84%
it doesn't work if we
make the correction.

00:16:35.680 --> 00:16:38.450 align:middle line:84%
And anyway, it's
going to come back

00:16:38.450 --> 00:16:40.940 align:middle line:90%
to where it was originally.

00:16:40.940 --> 00:16:43.340 align:middle line:90%
And there is no 13th sign.

00:16:43.340 --> 00:16:45.080 align:middle line:90%
I talk about that on my website.

00:16:45.080 --> 00:16:50.150 align:middle line:84%
And it's all connected to this
procession of the equinoxes,

00:16:50.150 --> 00:16:51.500 align:middle line:90%
where things are moving.

00:16:51.500 --> 00:16:54.980 align:middle line:84%
You do not get your personality
from the constellations.

00:16:54.980 --> 00:16:56.900 align:middle line:90%
You get them from the planets.

00:16:56.900 --> 00:17:00.590 align:middle line:84%
Think of the constellations as a
big tape measure that glitters,

00:17:00.590 --> 00:17:03.099 align:middle line:84%
and it's beautiful,
and its stars.

00:17:03.099 --> 00:17:05.390 align:middle line:84%
I used to think constellations
were all over the globe.

00:17:05.390 --> 00:17:06.250 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:17:06.250 --> 00:17:08.069 align:middle line:84%
They're only within
that golden belt.

00:17:08.069 --> 00:17:08.869 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ah.

00:17:08.869 --> 00:17:11.190 align:middle line:84%
So these are, what you
are talking about more,

00:17:11.190 --> 00:17:13.460 align:middle line:84%
are the personalities
of the sign.

00:17:13.460 --> 00:17:14.780 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: Yes, but everything.

00:17:14.780 --> 00:17:17.900 align:middle line:84%
Even the predictions
of when you'll

00:17:17.900 --> 00:17:22.700 align:middle line:84%
have a really rewarding
time or a challenging time,

00:17:22.700 --> 00:17:24.890 align:middle line:84%
it doesn't work when
we make the correction.

00:17:24.890 --> 00:17:26.300 align:middle line:90%
You can.

00:17:26.300 --> 00:17:29.240 align:middle line:84%
On any software program,
you can make it.

00:17:29.240 --> 00:17:30.590 align:middle line:90%
I could do it in two seconds.

00:17:30.590 --> 00:17:31.190 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I see.

00:17:31.190 --> 00:17:32.439 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: But it doesn't work.

00:17:32.439 --> 00:17:33.930 align:middle line:90%
We've tried it.

00:17:33.930 --> 00:17:35.810 align:middle line:84%
There's been white
papers written.

00:17:35.810 --> 00:17:38.030 align:middle line:84%
Western astrology does
not make the correction.

00:17:38.030 --> 00:17:39.620 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So what happens
when you see something

00:17:39.620 --> 00:17:41.600 align:middle line:84%
bad in someone's chart, where
they're going to be going

00:17:41.600 --> 00:17:43.040 align:middle line:90%
through a really rough time?

00:17:43.040 --> 00:17:44.280 align:middle line:90%
Do you tell them?

00:17:44.280 --> 00:17:45.500 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: Yeah, I do.

00:17:45.500 --> 00:17:47.550 align:middle line:84%
I say, you've got
to watch that job.

00:17:47.550 --> 00:17:52.080 align:middle line:84%
It could be that that company
may be merging or laying people

00:17:52.080 --> 00:17:52.880 align:middle line:90%
off.

00:17:52.880 --> 00:17:54.350 align:middle line:90%
You have to.

00:17:54.350 --> 00:17:56.970 align:middle line:84%
It's like letting your friend
go out, having lipstick,

00:17:56.970 --> 00:17:58.730 align:middle line:90%
like, all over her face.

00:17:58.730 --> 00:17:59.930 align:middle line:90%
It's not right.

00:17:59.930 --> 00:18:07.940 align:middle line:84%
You should tell them, but it's
so easy to overstate an aspect

00:18:07.940 --> 00:18:10.880 align:middle line:84%
and make it sound
worse than it is.

00:18:10.880 --> 00:18:16.310 align:middle line:84%
I've learned that things
aren't usually in the extreme.

00:18:16.310 --> 00:18:18.980 align:middle line:84%
You have to rein yourself
in if you're an astrologer,

00:18:18.980 --> 00:18:21.280 align:middle line:90%
and not go overboard.

00:18:21.280 --> 00:18:24.380 align:middle line:84%
There's this middle
course you have to take.

00:18:24.380 --> 00:18:26.930 align:middle line:90%
Eclipses are the most dramatic.

00:18:26.930 --> 00:18:27.890 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Why is that?

00:18:27.890 --> 00:18:28.973 align:middle line:90%
Let's talk about eclipses.

00:18:28.973 --> 00:18:32.730 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: Well, they
bring to the surface

00:18:32.730 --> 00:18:36.380 align:middle line:84%
things that are going on that
you had no idea were going on.

00:18:36.380 --> 00:18:38.780 align:middle line:90%
You can think of last summer.

00:18:38.780 --> 00:18:41.930 align:middle line:84%
July 27th was a very
difficult eclipse.

00:18:41.930 --> 00:18:46.640 align:middle line:84%
But then there was a very
good one on August 10th.

00:18:46.640 --> 00:18:48.980 align:middle line:84%
But sometimes you have
to give something up.

00:18:48.980 --> 00:18:52.490 align:middle line:84%
I sometimes say to myself,
OK, what is this eclipse going

00:18:52.490 --> 00:18:53.750 align:middle line:90%
to give to me?

00:18:53.750 --> 00:18:56.380 align:middle line:84%
It's going to ask for
a sacrificial lamb.

00:18:56.380 --> 00:18:58.280 align:middle line:84%
It's going to ask me
to give something up.

00:18:58.280 --> 00:19:00.860 align:middle line:84%
But it's going to give
me something, too.

00:19:00.860 --> 00:19:02.789 align:middle line:84%
Something ends and
something else begins.

00:19:02.789 --> 00:19:04.580 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's a good
way of looking at it.

00:19:04.580 --> 00:19:05.746 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: And you know what?

00:19:05.746 --> 00:19:08.060 align:middle line:84%
Until you can step back
and see the whole pattern,

00:19:08.060 --> 00:19:10.730 align:middle line:84%
you can't say if it was a
good eclipse or a bad eclipse.

00:19:10.730 --> 00:19:12.230 align:middle line:90%
You have to wait a little bit.

00:19:12.230 --> 00:19:16.160 align:middle line:84%
And you usually can
turn difficult things

00:19:16.160 --> 00:19:17.330 align:middle line:90%
into positive things.

00:19:17.330 --> 00:19:20.980 align:middle line:84%
The Chinese say in every
reversal is opportunity.

00:19:20.980 --> 00:19:22.990 align:middle line:90%
And it's so true.

00:19:22.990 --> 00:19:25.510 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Is a reversal
what the retrograde is?

00:19:25.510 --> 00:19:26.310 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: Oh, no.

00:19:26.310 --> 00:19:29.330 align:middle line:84%
[CHUCKLES] It just means
a setback or something

00:19:29.330 --> 00:19:32.060 align:middle line:90%
very difficult happening.

00:19:32.060 --> 00:19:33.737 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What is a
Mercury retrograde?

00:19:33.737 --> 00:19:36.320 align:middle line:84%
Tell me about that, because they
seem to wreak a lot of havoc.

00:19:36.320 --> 00:19:38.600 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: It does, because
it happens so often,

00:19:38.600 --> 00:19:41.210 align:middle line:90%
every 12 weeks.

00:19:41.210 --> 00:19:43.190 align:middle line:84%
Mercury is the
planet of intellect,

00:19:43.190 --> 00:19:46.520 align:middle line:84%
of communication,
negotiation, commerce, buying

00:19:46.520 --> 00:19:51.120 align:middle line:84%
and selling, transportation,
shipping, customs,

00:19:51.120 --> 00:19:52.016 align:middle line:90%
the post office.

00:19:52.016 --> 00:19:54.230 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHS] Sometimes you
hear of a letter coming

00:19:54.230 --> 00:19:57.740 align:middle line:90%
from 1942 getting delivered.

00:19:57.740 --> 00:20:01.600 align:middle line:84%
But there's such a cute
story about Little Mercury.

00:20:01.600 --> 00:20:02.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:20:02.580 --> 00:20:06.890 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: Now, remember,
Mercury rules Gemini and Virgo.

00:20:06.890 --> 00:20:09.260 align:middle line:84%
So those two are
affected the most.

00:20:09.260 --> 00:20:12.590 align:middle line:84%
So Little Mercury
wakes up in his cave.

00:20:12.590 --> 00:20:14.870 align:middle line:84%
And he's like, why are
we in a cave, Mama?

00:20:14.870 --> 00:20:15.760 align:middle line:90%
This is terrible.

00:20:15.760 --> 00:20:18.560 align:middle line:84%
He talks from day
one, real speech.

00:20:18.560 --> 00:20:23.450 align:middle line:84%
His mother is like, well,
had an affair with Zeus.

00:20:23.450 --> 00:20:25.862 align:middle line:84%
We're not going to
talk about this.

00:20:25.862 --> 00:20:26.690 align:middle line:90%
Shh.

00:20:26.690 --> 00:20:28.310 align:middle line:90%
And why are you talking at all?

00:20:28.310 --> 00:20:30.020 align:middle line:90%
You're an infant.

00:20:30.020 --> 00:20:32.320 align:middle line:84%
So the baby crawls
out of the bassinet.

00:20:32.320 --> 00:20:34.190 align:middle line:84%
Says, I'm not going
to live in this cave.

00:20:34.190 --> 00:20:37.250 align:middle line:84%
I want to be on Mount Olympus
with my brothers and sisters,

00:20:37.250 --> 00:20:40.550 align:middle line:84%
even if they're not full
brothers and sisters.

00:20:40.550 --> 00:20:43.490 align:middle line:90%
So he steals Apollo's cattle.

00:20:43.490 --> 00:20:45.620 align:middle line:90%
And farmer is there.

00:20:45.620 --> 00:20:49.580 align:middle line:84%
And he says, you didn't see
me take this cattle here.

00:20:49.580 --> 00:20:51.080 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to pay you.

00:20:51.080 --> 00:20:53.930 align:middle line:84%
He's a clever,
street-smart baby.

00:20:53.930 --> 00:20:56.750 align:middle line:84%
And he makes the
cattle walk backward,

00:20:56.750 --> 00:20:58.970 align:middle line:84%
Mercury retrograde
so that Apollo

00:20:58.970 --> 00:21:00.470 align:middle line:90%
won't know where his cattle is.

00:21:00.470 --> 00:21:05.550 align:middle line:84%
And he takes one steer, and he
chops him up, and offers him

00:21:05.550 --> 00:21:06.350 align:middle line:90%
to the gods.

00:21:06.350 --> 00:21:08.900 align:middle line:84%
This is considered
very sophisticated.

00:21:08.900 --> 00:21:11.570 align:middle line:84%
The next day, he goes back to
make sure there's no clues.

00:21:11.570 --> 00:21:12.890 align:middle line:90%
He sees the same farmer.

00:21:12.890 --> 00:21:14.720 align:middle line:84%
But he's shapeshifted
and he said, did you

00:21:14.720 --> 00:21:17.524 align:middle line:84%
see a baby stealing
Apollo's cattle?

00:21:17.524 --> 00:21:19.190 align:middle line:84%
And he said, oh, yeah,
he went that way.

00:21:19.190 --> 00:21:21.860 align:middle line:84%
He's like, I paid him off
I can't even trust him.

00:21:21.860 --> 00:21:23.870 align:middle line:90%
So he turns him into stone.

00:21:23.870 --> 00:21:27.950 align:middle line:84%
So now by this time, Apollo's
noticed his cattle is missing

00:21:27.950 --> 00:21:29.750 align:middle line:90%
and is looking everywhere.

00:21:29.750 --> 00:21:32.870 align:middle line:84%
And finally, he's following
the breadcrumbs, so to speak.

00:21:32.870 --> 00:21:35.500 align:middle line:84%
He comes into the cave
with his great light.

00:21:35.500 --> 00:21:40.050 align:middle line:84%
The mother was just in awe
and doesn't know what to say.

00:21:40.050 --> 00:21:42.530 align:middle line:84%
And the baby makes
believe he's sleeping.

00:21:42.530 --> 00:21:45.620 align:middle line:84%
And Apollo says, I
know what you did.

00:21:45.620 --> 00:21:47.390 align:middle line:84%
The baby sits up
and argues with him.

00:21:47.390 --> 00:21:48.800 align:middle line:90%
What did you expect?

00:21:48.800 --> 00:21:49.820 align:middle line:90%
Look at this place.

00:21:49.820 --> 00:21:50.630 align:middle line:90%
You live here?

00:21:50.630 --> 00:21:52.160 align:middle line:90%
You live on Mount Olympus.

00:21:52.160 --> 00:21:53.810 align:middle line:90%
Nobody would want to live here!

00:21:53.810 --> 00:21:54.950 align:middle line:90%
So he's amused by him.

00:21:54.950 --> 00:21:56.690 align:middle line:90%
He says, I'm taking you to Zeus.

00:21:56.690 --> 00:21:58.070 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what
to do with you.

00:21:58.070 --> 00:22:01.680 align:middle line:84%
So he picks up the baby,
brings him up to Mount Olympus.

00:22:01.680 --> 00:22:04.610 align:middle line:84%
Zeus looks at the baby
and sees how smart he is.

00:22:04.610 --> 00:22:08.730 align:middle line:84%
He also looks just like him,
so he can't really disavow him.

00:22:08.730 --> 00:22:10.640 align:middle line:84%
Zeus says, here's what
we're going to do.

00:22:10.640 --> 00:22:12.710 align:middle line:90%
You will live up here.

00:22:12.710 --> 00:22:16.250 align:middle line:84%
And you speak so well,
you will speak for me.

00:22:16.250 --> 00:22:18.500 align:middle line:90%
You will always sit next to me.

00:22:18.500 --> 00:22:21.620 align:middle line:84%
But when you go 27 and
1/2 degrees away from me,

00:22:21.620 --> 00:22:24.704 align:middle line:90%
I will yank you right back.

00:22:24.704 --> 00:22:26.120 align:middle line:84%
And you must stay
here, but I will

00:22:26.120 --> 00:22:29.450 align:middle line:84%
let you travel to Heaven,
to Earth, to Hades.

00:22:29.450 --> 00:22:32.810 align:middle line:84%
Every other planet had strict
rules on where they could go.

00:22:32.810 --> 00:22:36.770 align:middle line:84%
Mercury, being the travel
planet, could go anywhere.

00:22:36.770 --> 00:22:38.220 align:middle line:90%
But there is a price for this.

00:22:38.220 --> 00:22:39.140 align:middle line:90%
You have to--

00:22:39.140 --> 00:22:40.010 align:middle line:90%
I need you.

00:22:40.010 --> 00:22:42.030 align:middle line:90%
You need to speak for me.

00:22:42.030 --> 00:22:44.850 align:middle line:84%
So whenever Mercury starts
wandering away, he says,

00:22:44.850 --> 00:22:45.650 align:middle line:90%
where are you?

00:22:45.650 --> 00:22:46.460 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And then
that's what happens.

00:22:46.460 --> 00:22:47.810 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: You're coming back.

00:22:47.810 --> 00:22:50.146 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So the planet
of Mercury wreaks havoc

00:22:50.146 --> 00:22:51.020 align:middle line:90%
and then it pulls us.

00:22:51.020 --> 00:22:52.478 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: When he's
retrograde, you

00:22:52.478 --> 00:22:54.740 align:middle line:90%
should never buy electronics.

00:22:54.740 --> 00:22:56.540 align:middle line:84%
When you have
Mercury retrograde,

00:22:56.540 --> 00:22:59.180 align:middle line:84%
you're usually
calling the repairman.

00:22:59.180 --> 00:23:02.422 align:middle line:84%
My dishwasher, which
was fairly new,

00:23:02.422 --> 00:23:04.130 align:middle line:84%
something went wrong
with it, and the man

00:23:04.130 --> 00:23:06.290 align:middle line:84%
came up, and said you
need a special part.

00:23:06.290 --> 00:23:09.920 align:middle line:84%
My TV, which I don't even use
that much in that one room--

00:23:09.920 --> 00:23:11.090 align:middle line:90%
it's a guest room--

00:23:11.090 --> 00:23:12.740 align:middle line:90%
conked out.

00:23:12.740 --> 00:23:17.420 align:middle line:84%
And you're not allowed to
buy a new electronic during.

00:23:17.420 --> 00:23:19.700 align:middle line:84%
So it's kind of
like, oh no, I have

00:23:19.700 --> 00:23:22.630 align:middle line:84%
to live like this for
another 2 and 1/2 weeks.

00:23:22.630 --> 00:23:25.256 align:middle line:84%
Mercury stays retrograde
for 3 and 1/2 weeks.

00:23:25.256 --> 00:23:26.880 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's an
eternity at the time.

00:23:26.880 --> 00:23:28.070 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: It does feel that way.

00:23:28.070 --> 00:23:30.530 align:middle line:84%
If someone's listening and says,
wait a minute, I'm pregnant

00:23:30.530 --> 00:23:32.480 align:middle line:84%
and I'm going to have my
baby with Mercury retrograde,

00:23:32.480 --> 00:23:32.810 align:middle line:90%
not to worry.

00:23:32.810 --> 00:23:34.184 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I was
going to say, yeah.

00:23:34.184 --> 00:23:37.100 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: I'm born with
Mercury retrograde.

00:23:37.100 --> 00:23:39.020 align:middle line:84%
It makes a child
more philosophical

00:23:39.020 --> 00:23:40.662 align:middle line:90%
because they think deeply.

00:23:40.662 --> 00:23:42.620 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I mean, we have
production that goes on

00:23:42.620 --> 00:23:43.320 align:middle line:90%
during Mercury retrograde.

00:23:43.320 --> 00:23:44.361 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: Oh, it's tough.

00:23:44.361 --> 00:23:45.620 align:middle line:90%
TV and publishing.

00:23:45.620 --> 00:23:46.730 align:middle line:90%
Very difficult.

00:23:46.730 --> 00:23:47.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, it is.

00:23:47.580 --> 00:23:50.240 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: Yeah there's
a lot of do-overs.

00:23:50.240 --> 00:23:54.260 align:middle line:84%
And I always tell
tech not to upgrade

00:23:54.260 --> 00:23:58.150 align:middle line:84%
the servers or the computers,
and they laugh at me.

00:23:58.150 --> 00:23:59.320 align:middle line:90%
Now they call me.

00:23:59.320 --> 00:24:01.250 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:24:01.250 --> 00:24:03.370 align:middle line:84%
I tell lawyers, I'm
not signing contracts

00:24:03.370 --> 00:24:04.370 align:middle line:90%
with Mercury retrograde.

00:24:04.370 --> 00:24:06.560 align:middle line:84%
They'll only have to
be renegotiated later.

00:24:06.560 --> 00:24:08.480 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you really
honestly live by it?

00:24:08.480 --> 00:24:10.220 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: Oh, yeah, I'm a
person of integrity, sure.

00:24:10.220 --> 00:24:12.170 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you plan
everything based on this?

00:24:12.170 --> 00:24:13.990 align:middle line:84%
Your schedule, your
lunches, everything?

00:24:13.990 --> 00:24:16.910 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: I kind of know
because I write a calendar.

00:24:16.910 --> 00:24:20.870 align:middle line:84%
So I know what the year
is going to be like.

00:24:20.870 --> 00:24:25.070 align:middle line:84%
For example, my daughter
was going to get married.

00:24:25.070 --> 00:24:31.040 align:middle line:90%
And she wanted a wonderful day.

00:24:31.040 --> 00:24:35.122 align:middle line:84%
And her boyfriend, who she was
living with at the time, Leo,

00:24:35.122 --> 00:24:36.830 align:middle line:84%
and his friends were
saying, when are you

00:24:36.830 --> 00:24:37.996 align:middle line:90%
and Christy getting married?

00:24:37.996 --> 00:24:41.000 align:middle line:84%
And I'm starting to feel
bad I hadn't a day yet.

00:24:41.000 --> 00:24:45.770 align:middle line:84%
But I saw this one year was
very good in the beginning

00:24:45.770 --> 00:24:49.724 align:middle line:84%
and very awful from June on
with too many retrogrades.

00:24:49.724 --> 00:24:51.890 align:middle line:84%
You don't want to get married
with Venus retrograde.

00:24:51.890 --> 00:24:53.390 align:middle line:90%
Affection cools.

00:24:53.390 --> 00:24:55.700 align:middle line:84%
Now, with Mercury retrograde,
because it's a pact,

00:24:55.700 --> 00:24:57.341 align:middle line:84%
it's a promise, you
don't want that.

00:24:57.341 --> 00:24:59.090 align:middle line:84%
And you don't want
Mars retrograde either,

00:24:59.090 --> 00:25:00.923 align:middle line:84%
because then there'd
be no sex after awhile.

00:25:00.923 --> 00:25:02.130 align:middle line:90%
It would be terrible.

00:25:02.130 --> 00:25:03.780 align:middle line:90%
So I couldn't do that to her.

00:25:03.780 --> 00:25:05.960 align:middle line:84%
And so I'm going
through all this.

00:25:05.960 --> 00:25:08.300 align:middle line:84%
Now, here's an
interesting statistic.

00:25:08.300 --> 00:25:10.940 align:middle line:84%
Most brides marry within
six weeks of the birthday.

00:25:10.940 --> 00:25:13.450 align:middle line:90%
So I started with that.

00:25:13.450 --> 00:25:17.000 align:middle line:84%
And I found an ideal day
very close to her birthday,

00:25:17.000 --> 00:25:18.740 align:middle line:84%
because it's the sun
conjuncts the sun.

00:25:18.740 --> 00:25:20.390 align:middle line:90%
It's coming together.

00:25:20.390 --> 00:25:25.430 align:middle line:84%
Most people marry the son
of their mother or father.

00:25:25.430 --> 00:25:27.380 align:middle line:84%
Now, Christy read
that and told me that.

00:25:27.380 --> 00:25:28.480 align:middle line:90%
I said, that's not true.

00:25:28.480 --> 00:25:33.260 align:middle line:84%
Said, mommy, you
married a Scorpio.

00:25:33.260 --> 00:25:35.240 align:middle line:90%
Grandpa is a Scorpio.

00:25:35.240 --> 00:25:37.040 align:middle line:90%
Great grandmother is a Scorpio.

00:25:37.040 --> 00:25:39.230 align:middle line:90%
I'm like, oh my gosh.

00:25:39.230 --> 00:25:40.860 align:middle line:90%
It happened to me.

00:25:40.860 --> 00:25:42.650 align:middle line:84%
So I want everyone
to think about it.

00:25:42.650 --> 00:25:44.780 align:middle line:84%
And you say, why
does this happen?

00:25:44.780 --> 00:25:47.030 align:middle line:84%
It's because you're
familiar with the sign.

00:25:47.030 --> 00:25:50.240 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Right, and the negatives
and the positives of the sign.

00:25:50.240 --> 00:25:51.740 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: There's
a certain comfort.

00:25:51.740 --> 00:25:54.390 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Now, in your own
life, you use this, obviously,

00:25:54.390 --> 00:25:56.300 align:middle line:90%
and you write a year ahead.

00:25:56.300 --> 00:26:00.092 align:middle line:84%
Can you tell us about
a year ahead, 2019?

00:26:00.092 --> 00:26:02.300 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: Oh, it's going to
be a more productive year

00:26:02.300 --> 00:26:04.656 align:middle line:84%
than last year, because we
had all those retrogrades.

00:26:04.656 --> 00:26:06.530 align:middle line:84%
Now, you say, well,
every planet retrogrades.

00:26:06.530 --> 00:26:07.330 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:26:07.330 --> 00:26:09.920 align:middle line:84%
The outer planets,
when they retrograde,

00:26:09.920 --> 00:26:12.140 align:middle line:90%
you don't feel them as strongly.

00:26:12.140 --> 00:26:17.180 align:middle line:84%
Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus,
Neptune, and Pluto.

00:26:17.180 --> 00:26:19.280 align:middle line:84%
You don't feel them
as strongly as you

00:26:19.280 --> 00:26:22.400 align:middle line:84%
do Venus, Mercury,
and Mars, because they

00:26:22.400 --> 00:26:25.530 align:middle line:90%
orbit close to Earth.

00:26:25.530 --> 00:26:27.690 align:middle line:84%
You can even see them
with the naked eye.

00:26:27.690 --> 00:26:31.060 align:middle line:84%
So you really don't want
to do big initiations

00:26:31.060 --> 00:26:32.060 align:middle line:90%
when they're retrograde.

00:26:32.060 --> 00:26:36.380 align:middle line:84%
Next year, Venus and
Mars are perfect.

00:26:36.380 --> 00:26:39.350 align:middle line:84%
Now, of course, little Mercury,
little Dennis the Menace,

00:26:39.350 --> 00:26:42.300 align:middle line:90%
he's going to go back and forth.

00:26:42.300 --> 00:26:44.510 align:middle line:84%
But for all practical
purposes, it's

00:26:44.510 --> 00:26:47.720 align:middle line:90%
a much more productive year.

00:26:47.720 --> 00:26:50.660 align:middle line:84%
The year before this was a
year of looking back a lot.

00:26:50.660 --> 00:26:52.310 align:middle line:10%
When the planet goes
retrograde, you're

00:26:52.310 --> 00:26:56.420 align:middle line:10%
supposed to think
about what went wrong,

00:26:56.420 --> 00:26:59.660 align:middle line:10%
how can I fix it,
where am I vulnerable,

00:26:59.660 --> 00:27:00.894 align:middle line:10%
and make corrections.

00:27:00.894 --> 00:27:02.810 align:middle line:84%
And most people don't
want to hear about that.

00:27:02.810 --> 00:27:03.920 align:middle line:90%
Let me forge forward.

00:27:03.920 --> 00:27:05.270 align:middle line:90%
We're human.

00:27:05.270 --> 00:27:09.420 align:middle line:84%
But yes, there are times in
our life we need to look back.

00:27:09.420 --> 00:27:10.260 align:middle line:90%
It's good for us.

00:27:10.260 --> 00:27:11.060 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:27:11.060 --> 00:27:13.370 align:middle line:90%
So 2019 is more looking ahead.

00:27:13.370 --> 00:27:14.330 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: Forward, mhm.

00:27:14.330 --> 00:27:15.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Progress?

00:27:15.690 --> 00:27:19.940 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: Yeah, well, Jupiter's
in Sagittarius, which rules

00:27:19.940 --> 00:27:21.335 align:middle line:90%
broadcasting and publishing.

00:27:21.335 --> 00:27:22.460 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Fantastic for Gaia.

