>>LISA: Now we have this
great quality production.

00:27:46.173 --> 00:27:47.050 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: Yes.

00:27:47.050 --> 00:27:49.100 align:middle line:84%
And you'll see
more and more that.

00:27:49.100 --> 00:27:51.500 align:middle line:90%
And then magazines have died.

00:27:51.500 --> 00:27:53.210 align:middle line:90%
I make my living in magazines.

00:27:53.210 --> 00:27:55.910 align:middle line:84%
I write for 10
different magazines.

00:27:55.910 --> 00:27:58.310 align:middle line:90%
And it is a suffering industry.

00:27:58.310 --> 00:28:01.700 align:middle line:84%
But with Jupiter and
Sagittarius, it just went in,

00:28:01.700 --> 00:28:04.370 align:middle line:84%
and it will stay all
the way through 2019

00:28:04.370 --> 00:28:06.320 align:middle line:90%
until the beginning of December.

00:28:06.320 --> 00:28:10.310 align:middle line:84%
And that's a very hopeful
placement for Jupiter.

00:28:10.310 --> 00:28:11.560 align:middle line:90%
It took 12 years to get there.

00:28:11.560 --> 00:28:13.809 align:middle line:84%
Of course, if you're a Sagg,
it's the best thing ever.

00:28:13.809 --> 00:28:15.290 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Now, what
does that mean?

00:28:15.290 --> 00:28:17.290 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: Jupiter's the
giver of gifts and luck.

00:28:17.290 --> 00:28:19.700 align:middle line:90%
Whatever he touches, it expands.

00:28:19.700 --> 00:28:23.090 align:middle line:84%
And it puts you at the right
place at the right time

00:28:23.090 --> 00:28:24.860 align:middle line:90%
with the right idea.

00:28:24.860 --> 00:28:27.147 align:middle line:90%
And it's just magical.

00:28:27.147 --> 00:28:27.980 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Fascinating.

00:28:27.980 --> 00:28:30.460 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: And you usually
travel a lot more if, say,

00:28:30.460 --> 00:28:33.297 align:middle line:84%
