00:33:21.655 --> 00:33:24.030 align:middle line:84%
But when you get to the other
side, the bridge falls away

00:33:24.030 --> 00:33:26.160 align:middle line:90%
and there's no way back.

00:33:26.160 --> 00:33:29.820 align:middle line:84%
You have to accept the
finality of an eclipse.

00:33:29.820 --> 00:33:32.190 align:middle line:84%
And don't lose your
dignity and beg.

00:33:32.190 --> 00:33:33.490 align:middle line:90%
It's not going to work.

00:33:33.490 --> 00:33:35.820 align:middle line:84%
It never does, because the
whole idea of an eclipse

00:33:35.820 --> 00:33:37.500 align:middle line:90%
is to push you forward.

00:33:37.500 --> 00:33:39.360 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Or don't have
significant events

00:33:39.360 --> 00:33:40.290 align:middle line:90%
during the eclipses.

00:33:40.290 --> 00:33:43.500 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: Well, it would
be best not to get married

00:33:43.500 --> 00:33:44.300 align:middle line:90%
on an eclipse--

00:33:44.300 --> 00:33:45.133 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Or break up.

00:33:45.133 --> 00:33:47.790 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: --or start a
business on an eclipse.

00:33:47.790 --> 00:33:50.714 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So are you talking about
lunar eclipses, solar eclipses?

00:33:50.714 --> 00:33:51.630 align:middle line:90%
What's the difference?

00:33:51.630 --> 00:33:52.430 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: Both.

00:33:52.430 --> 00:33:55.530 align:middle line:84%
In a typical year, we
have two lunar, two solar.

00:33:55.530 --> 00:33:59.150 align:middle line:84%
Actually in the coming
year, we have five.

00:33:59.150 --> 00:34:02.300 align:middle line:84%
A lunar eclipse is
always a full moon.

00:34:02.300 --> 00:34:05.310 align:middle line:84%
A solar eclipse is
always a new moon.

00:34:05.310 --> 00:34:09.260 align:middle line:84%
But they're normal, new,
and full moons on steroids.

00:34:09.260 --> 00:34:14.370 align:middle line:84%
They're three times as strong
as a normal average one is.

00:34:14.370 --> 00:34:18.120 align:middle line:84%
And as an astrologer, I
look to those eclipses

00:34:18.120 --> 00:34:21.750 align:middle line:84%
to see where the biggest
change is going to happen

00:34:21.750 --> 00:34:24.010 align:middle line:90%
in someone's life that year.

00:34:24.010 --> 00:34:25.679 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Now, what
about astrology

00:34:25.679 --> 00:34:29.439 align:middle line:84%
doesn't have anything to do with
freewill or your own choices

00:34:29.439 --> 00:34:30.239 align:middle line:90%
in life?

00:34:30.239 --> 00:34:33.719 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: Tremendously, it
has to do with freewill.

00:34:33.719 --> 00:34:36.270 align:middle line:10%
I could tell you
it's a good time

00:34:36.270 --> 00:34:38.580 align:middle line:10%
to start looking
for an apartment.

00:34:38.580 --> 00:34:42.780 align:middle line:10%
But if you say, I'm fine, I like
where I live, you can renovate.

00:34:42.780 --> 00:34:43.679 align:middle line:90%
You can pay.

00:34:43.679 --> 00:34:45.239 align:middle line:90%
You could do repairs.

00:34:45.239 --> 00:34:47.760 align:middle line:84%
If you say, no, I don't
really have any money,

00:34:47.760 --> 00:34:51.239 align:middle line:84%
then take a look out
in the flea markets.

00:34:51.239 --> 00:34:53.580 align:middle line:84%
You may get the
most beautiful desk

00:34:53.580 --> 00:34:56.489 align:middle line:84%
that you've been looking
for at a bargain price.

00:34:56.489 --> 00:34:59.130 align:middle line:84%
You can update your
everyday dishes.

00:34:59.130 --> 00:35:02.070 align:middle line:84%
You can do things on a
little scale or big scale.

00:35:02.070 --> 00:35:05.140 align:middle line:84%
Also, when you have
a good house of home,

00:35:05.140 --> 00:35:07.080 align:middle line:84%
you also get great
family support, too.

00:35:07.080 --> 00:35:09.660 align:middle line:84%
And your parents help you,
and give you great advice,

00:35:09.660 --> 00:35:11.820 align:middle line:84%
and may even loan you
money if you need it.

00:35:11.820 --> 00:35:13.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So many
people may not ever

00:35:13.800 --> 00:35:15.240 align:middle line:90%
look to astrology for answers.

00:35:15.240 --> 00:35:16.860 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: Oh, yeah,
you don't have to.

00:35:16.860 --> 00:35:18.540 align:middle line:90%
I'm not an evangelist.

00:35:18.540 --> 00:35:20.490 align:middle line:84%
But I feel it's
such an advantage

00:35:20.490 --> 00:35:23.490 align:middle line:84%
to know where your
areas of strength are.

00:35:23.490 --> 00:35:27.960 align:middle line:84%
And we're also focused on
things that are frustrating us.

00:35:27.960 --> 00:35:31.620 align:middle line:84%
When all these things over here
are growing in your garden,

00:35:31.620 --> 00:35:33.390 align:middle line:90%
pick that plum off the tree.

00:35:33.390 --> 00:35:34.890 align:middle line:90%
It's there for you.

00:35:34.890 --> 00:35:36.720 align:middle line:90%
Look at the whole 360.

00:35:36.720 --> 00:35:38.220 align:middle line:90%
I can show it to you.

00:35:38.220 --> 00:35:40.830 align:middle line:84%
I can tell you when to
act, when to hold back.

00:35:40.830 --> 00:35:44.520 align:middle line:90%
But in the end, it's up to you.

00:35:44.520 --> 00:35:46.440 align:middle line:84%
Reporters lately
have been saying,

00:35:46.440 --> 00:35:51.150 align:middle line:84%
is astrology popular because
no one believes in God anymore?

00:35:51.150 --> 00:35:54.940 align:middle line:84%
I said, you just put a steel
blade through my heart.

00:35:54.940 --> 00:35:57.810 align:middle line:84%
I would never, ever
be in a discipline

00:35:57.810 --> 00:35:59.910 align:middle line:90%
that was anti-religion.

00:35:59.910 --> 00:36:03.240 align:middle line:84%
Religion teaches us ethics,
how to treat each other,

00:36:03.240 --> 00:36:06.570 align:middle line:84%
how to realize that there is
a force bigger than ourselves

00:36:06.570 --> 00:36:09.480 align:middle line:84%
that has created
this beautiful world.

00:36:09.480 --> 00:36:13.350 align:middle line:84%
Actually, in the chart, it shows
your feelings toward religion.

00:36:13.350 --> 00:36:15.120 align:middle line:90%
The ninth house is the dogma.

00:36:15.120 --> 00:36:17.700 align:middle line:90%
The 12th house is your belief.

00:36:17.700 --> 00:36:20.860 align:middle line:84%
So there's a lot of
misconceptions out there.

00:36:20.860 --> 00:36:23.940 align:middle line:84%
And people say, don't tell me
I'm going to be hit by a truck.

00:36:23.940 --> 00:36:24.850 align:middle line:90%
It's not like that.

00:36:24.850 --> 00:36:25.230 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You're never
going to say that.

00:36:25.230 --> 00:36:26.544 align:middle line:90%
You're always so positive.

00:36:26.544 --> 00:36:28.710 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: [LAUGHS] Well,
it's because Little Mom was

00:36:28.710 --> 00:36:29.310 align:middle line:90%
so positive.

00:36:29.310 --> 00:36:30.030 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:36:30.030 --> 00:36:31.571 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That helps
in a good teacher.

00:36:31.571 --> 00:36:32.955 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: Yes.

00:36:32.955 --> 00:36:35.940 align:middle line:84%
However, having said
that, big life events

00:36:35.940 --> 00:36:38.730 align:middle line:90%
happen very near eclipses.

00:36:38.730 --> 00:36:39.960 align:middle line:90%
They do.

00:36:39.960 --> 00:36:43.210 align:middle line:84%
Now, It was funny, this
past couple of years,

00:36:43.210 --> 00:36:44.790 align:middle line:90%
I had an operation.

00:36:44.790 --> 00:36:47.250 align:middle line:90%
And the doctor picked June 12th.

00:36:47.250 --> 00:36:50.427 align:middle line:90%
I'm like, such a random day.

00:36:50.427 --> 00:36:51.260 align:middle line:90%
It's not a new moon.

00:36:51.260 --> 00:36:52.260 align:middle line:90%
It's not a full moon.

00:36:52.260 --> 00:36:53.210 align:middle line:90%
And I had to get two doctors--

00:36:53.210 --> 00:36:54.380 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I doubt he's looking.

00:36:54.380 --> 00:36:55.254 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: Oh, I know.

00:36:55.254 --> 00:36:56.280 align:middle line:90%
He wasn't looking.

00:36:56.280 --> 00:36:59.450 align:middle line:84%
But then I realized the
next month was July 12th,

00:36:59.450 --> 00:37:01.430 align:middle line:90%
and that was an eclipse.

00:37:01.430 --> 00:37:03.350 align:middle line:84%
So an eclipse can
affect you one month

00:37:03.350 --> 00:37:06.080 align:middle line:84%
to the day early or one
month to the day later.

00:37:06.080 --> 00:37:07.040 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh.

00:37:07.040 --> 00:37:08.960 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: So when you
have a very big event,

00:37:08.960 --> 00:37:11.870 align:middle line:84%
just scribble down on your
calendar the day it happened.

00:37:11.870 --> 00:37:14.300 align:middle line:90%
You won't remember a year later.

00:37:14.300 --> 00:37:17.900 align:middle line:84%
And often, I'm asking you
to look back in my column.

00:37:17.900 --> 00:37:20.560 align:middle line:84%
I write 40,000 words
a month, my monthly.

00:37:20.560 --> 00:37:23.090 align:middle line:84%
My monthly is what
put me on the map,

00:37:23.090 --> 00:37:24.620 align:middle line:90%
because people like the detail.

00:37:24.620 --> 00:37:28.790 align:middle line:84%
And the average person
comes in 3.2 times.

00:37:28.790 --> 00:37:32.570 align:middle line:84%
So I want you to keep a
little bit of a record.

00:37:32.570 --> 00:37:35.120 align:middle line:84%
I know Oprah tells you to
write journals, but most of us

00:37:35.120 --> 00:37:37.290 align:middle line:90%
don't have time to do that.

00:37:37.290 --> 00:37:40.910 align:middle line:84%
People have children, and jobs,
and they have things to do.

00:37:40.910 --> 00:37:44.300 align:middle line:84%
So just write, met a
new person, or signed

00:37:44.300 --> 00:37:46.400 align:middle line:84%
my lease on my apartment,
or whatever it is.

00:37:46.400 --> 00:37:48.645 align:middle line:84%
Whatever's big, just
make a note of it.

00:37:48.645 --> 00:37:49.520 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: On calendars.

00:37:49.520 --> 00:37:51.561 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: It's kind of
fun at the end of the year

00:37:51.561 --> 00:37:53.750 align:middle line:84%
to look back and see
what happened that year.

00:37:53.750 --> 00:37:55.950 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So why does it
impact a month before

00:37:55.950 --> 00:37:57.200 align:middle line:90%
and a month after to the date?

00:37:57.200 --> 00:38:00.560 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: Because we
deal with bell curves.

00:38:00.560 --> 00:38:03.810 align:middle line:84%
Astrologers are dealing with--
it's part of the algorithm.

00:38:03.810 --> 00:38:04.610 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:38:04.610 --> 00:38:06.650 align:middle line:90%
So it can impact either way.

00:38:06.650 --> 00:38:08.934 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: And you think, oh,
I've avoided the eclipse,

00:38:08.934 --> 00:38:10.475 align:middle line:84%
and it's the month
to the day before.

00:38:10.475 --> 00:38:13.040 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS] It's OK, though.

00:38:13.040 --> 00:38:14.600 align:middle line:90%
I like that kind of separation.

00:38:14.600 --> 00:38:15.700 align:middle line:90%
It's OK.

00:38:15.700 --> 00:38:17.325 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And then what
about full moons?

00:38:17.325 --> 00:38:18.770 align:middle line:90%
What's an intention?

00:38:18.770 --> 00:38:21.650 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: A full moon will
bring everybody together,

00:38:21.650 --> 00:38:25.460 align:middle line:84%
tremendous energy, and it
will give you a conclusion.

00:38:25.460 --> 00:38:28.400 align:middle line:84%
And it may be something you've
been working on six months

00:38:28.400 --> 00:38:32.240 align:middle line:84%
ahead, because the new
moon, let's say in Ares

00:38:32.240 --> 00:38:35.150 align:middle line:84%
might be in April, but
the full moon in Ares

00:38:35.150 --> 00:38:37.490 align:middle line:90%
won't be until October.

00:38:37.490 --> 00:38:40.570 align:middle line:84%
So let's say you're
trying for a hard job.

00:38:40.570 --> 00:38:43.760 align:middle line:84%
Lots of people want it, and
you don't want to be annoying.

00:38:43.760 --> 00:38:46.580 align:middle line:84%
So you want to call up
right before a full moon

00:38:46.580 --> 00:38:49.250 align:middle line:84%
because they're
coming to a collusion.

00:38:49.250 --> 00:38:51.740 align:middle line:84%
I tell you in my column
when to make those calls,

00:38:51.740 --> 00:38:54.660 align:middle line:84%
because you want to do
it at the right time.

00:38:54.660 --> 00:38:56.646 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So do you
set intentions?

00:38:56.646 --> 00:38:58.520 align:middle line:84%
Because I'm always called
to that beautiful--

00:38:58.520 --> 00:38:59.320 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: No.

00:38:59.320 --> 00:39:00.560 align:middle line:90%
A new moon, you plant things.

00:39:00.560 --> 00:39:01.360 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, OK.

00:39:01.360 --> 00:39:04.280 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: A full moon is
really the culmination

00:39:04.280 --> 00:39:08.750 align:middle line:84%
of all your hard work, although
my book came out on a new moon.

00:39:08.750 --> 00:39:10.340 align:middle line:90%
That means a new beginning.

00:39:10.340 --> 00:39:14.120 align:middle line:84%
And if my publisher is
happy, which is Meredith,

00:39:14.120 --> 00:39:16.730 align:middle line:84%
it means the fact that my
book came out on the new moon

00:39:16.730 --> 00:39:20.150 align:middle line:84%
suggests that if
I do a good job,

00:39:20.150 --> 00:39:22.920 align:middle line:84%
I'll get another offer
to do another book.

00:39:22.920 --> 00:39:26.420 align:middle line:84%
So on a full moon,
it just means you'll

00:39:26.420 --> 00:39:29.630 align:middle line:84%
get a lot of press attention
and things like that.

00:39:29.630 --> 00:39:32.739 align:middle line:84%
There's a big spotlight
that goes on in a full moon.

00:39:32.739 --> 00:39:34.280 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But in a
new moon, it means--

00:39:34.280 --> 00:39:35.930 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: It's time
to plant seeds.

00:39:35.930 --> 00:39:36.810 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:39:36.810 --> 00:39:37.610 align:middle line:90%
Good to know.

00:39:37.610 --> 00:39:39.720 align:middle line:84%
So intention-setting at
that time is a good idea.

00:39:39.720 --> 00:39:40.520 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: Yeah.

00:39:40.520 --> 00:39:44.060 align:middle line:90%
You have to know what you want.

00:39:44.060 --> 00:39:45.890 align:middle line:84%
Time can go through
your fingers.

00:39:45.890 --> 00:39:47.930 align:middle line:90%
You really need markers.

00:39:47.930 --> 00:39:49.400 align:middle line:90%
And astrology gives you that.

00:39:49.400 --> 00:39:52.580 align:middle line:84%
And every month, I tell
you what that new moon

00:39:52.580 --> 00:39:57.870 align:middle line:84%
will help you with it's
usually a very specific part

00:39:57.870 --> 00:39:58.670 align:middle line:90%
of your life.

00:39:58.670 --> 00:40:03.170 align:middle line:84%
To look for an apartment,
to start dating again,

00:40:03.170 --> 00:40:04.550 align:middle line:90%
to get a new job.

00:40:04.550 --> 00:40:07.550 align:middle line:84%
But there's one new moon a year
that happens at birthday time

00:40:07.550 --> 00:40:10.970 align:middle line:84%
that you can use like a gift
certificate anywhere you want.

00:40:10.970 --> 00:40:13.100 align:middle line:84%
The universe wants to see
what's important to you,

00:40:13.100 --> 00:40:15.050 align:middle line:90%
so you direct it where you want.

00:40:15.050 --> 00:40:17.000 align:middle line:84%
But you have to act right
after that new moon.

00:40:17.000 --> 00:40:18.650 align:middle line:90%
Not before.

00:40:18.650 --> 00:40:20.280 align:middle line:90%
Right after.

00:40:20.280 --> 00:40:22.250 align:middle line:84%
And then it's the
strongest at the beginning,

00:40:22.250 --> 00:40:26.630 align:middle line:84%
and then it peters slightly
until we get to the full moon,

00:40:26.630 --> 00:40:28.880 align:middle line:90%
and she's spent all her energy.

00:40:28.880 --> 00:40:32.780 align:middle line:84%
The beautiful white
moon, who comes

00:40:32.780 --> 00:40:35.120 align:middle line:84%
in her gown and
her white gloves.

00:40:35.120 --> 00:40:40.970 align:middle line:84%
And she's now tuckered out
and needs her sleeping beauty.

00:40:40.970 --> 00:40:43.200 align:middle line:84%
And then the full moon
comes in to take her place.

00:40:43.200 --> 00:40:44.000 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:40:44.000 --> 00:40:45.670 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I love that you
personify planets and moons.

00:40:45.670 --> 00:40:47.300 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: Oh, I think of
them as little people.

00:40:47.300 --> 00:40:48.101 align:middle line:90%
I talk to them.

00:40:48.101 --> 00:40:48.900 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:40:48.900 --> 00:40:50.082 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You do, don't you?

00:40:50.082 --> 00:40:50.999 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: I love them.

00:40:50.999 --> 00:40:52.831 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, you have
to to do what you do.

00:40:52.831 --> 00:40:53.690 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: Yeah.

00:40:53.690 --> 00:40:57.740 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Now, do you ever see
significant events happening,

00:40:57.740 --> 00:41:00.340 align:middle line:84%
like the Me Too movement
or significant movements?

00:41:00.340 --> 00:41:04.430 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: Well, it's amazing
about the Me Too movement.

00:41:04.430 --> 00:41:06.790 align:middle line:84%
Jupiter is not only the
giver of gifts and life,

00:41:06.790 --> 00:41:08.990 align:middle line:90%
but the great healer.

00:41:08.990 --> 00:41:12.500 align:middle line:84%
And he rules sex,
money, and power.

00:41:12.500 --> 00:41:20.500 align:middle line:90%
He came in October 10th of 2017.

00:41:20.500 --> 00:41:22.450 align:middle line:90%
And almost a week later--

00:41:22.450 --> 00:41:24.640 align:middle line:84%
I don't know when Mr.
Weinstein hit the news,

00:41:24.640 --> 00:41:29.860 align:middle line:84%
but it was within 10
days or two weeks.

00:41:29.860 --> 00:41:33.310 align:middle line:84%
And it caused a
sociological shift,

00:41:33.310 --> 00:41:37.120 align:middle line:84%
the likes of which I wouldn't
have thought possible.

00:41:37.120 --> 00:41:38.470 align:middle line:90%
And it's still going on.

00:41:38.470 --> 00:41:40.250 align:middle line:90%
We're still hearing things.

00:41:40.250 --> 00:41:42.010 align:middle line:84%
And different
industries are falling

00:41:42.010 --> 00:41:44.950 align:middle line:84%
like dominoes, because
entertainment was first--

00:41:44.950 --> 00:41:47.020 align:middle line:84%
and music, of
course-- but there's

00:41:47.020 --> 00:41:48.550 align:middle line:84%
going to be other
industries, too.

00:41:48.550 --> 00:41:50.462 align:middle line:90%
So it's not going to be over.

00:41:50.462 --> 00:41:51.670 align:middle line:90%
But you're going to want to--

00:41:51.670 --> 00:41:53.001 align:middle line:90%
Jupiter brings justice.

00:41:53.001 --> 00:41:54.750 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Having voices
heard, and so forth.

00:41:54.750 --> 00:41:56.500 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: And it's
heartbreaking at times.

00:41:56.500 --> 00:42:00.070 align:middle line:84%
Somebody like Charlie
Rose, who I always enjoyed

00:42:00.070 --> 00:42:02.740 align:middle line:90%
his documentaries, I miss them.

00:42:02.740 --> 00:42:03.900 align:middle line:90%
But then I understand.

00:42:03.900 --> 00:42:04.732 align:middle line:84%
