00:50:03.760 --> 00:50:06.280 align:middle line:84%
And then you grow up and
you don't listen to that

00:50:06.280 --> 00:50:09.610 align:middle line:84%
because you're contributing
something else to the world.

00:50:09.610 --> 00:50:12.970 align:middle line:84%
Those fresh eyes
are so precious,

00:50:12.970 --> 00:50:14.950 align:middle line:84%
because as you're
growing up, you're

00:50:14.950 --> 00:50:16.480 align:middle line:84%
seeing what's wrong
with the world.

00:50:16.480 --> 00:50:20.710 align:middle line:84%
And you can be one of the people
that helps to add and improve

00:50:20.710 --> 00:50:21.970 align:middle line:90%
the world.

00:50:21.970 --> 00:50:25.090 align:middle line:84%
But you shouldn't listen
to what your mother tells

00:50:25.090 --> 00:50:28.810 align:middle line:84%
you, or your professor,
or your best friend.

00:50:28.810 --> 00:50:31.672 align:middle line:90%
Do what you're passionate about.

00:50:31.672 --> 00:50:33.880 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What does it mean
when someone's on the cusp?

00:50:33.880 --> 00:50:36.160 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: It means
that they're born

00:50:36.160 --> 00:50:39.130 align:middle line:84%
right about when the
sun is about to move

00:50:39.130 --> 00:50:41.950 align:middle line:90%
into the next constellation.

00:50:41.950 --> 00:50:43.950 align:middle line:84%
And the cusp babies
always feel like they're

00:50:43.950 --> 00:50:47.440 align:middle line:84%
nobody's child, when in
fact, they're the luckiest.

00:50:47.440 --> 00:50:49.990 align:middle line:90%
Like, let's take November 22nd.

00:50:49.990 --> 00:50:52.570 align:middle line:84%
They take all the
best from Scorpio.

00:50:52.570 --> 00:50:55.550 align:middle line:84%
The shrewdness, the
good business sense,

00:50:55.550 --> 00:51:00.190 align:middle line:84%
the fabulous negotiation,
the determination and passion

00:51:00.190 --> 00:51:01.840 align:middle line:90%
of Scorpio.

00:51:01.840 --> 00:51:06.850 align:middle line:84%
And all the philosophy, and
optimism of Sagittarius,

00:51:06.850 --> 00:51:09.580 align:middle line:84%
and the love of travel,
and cultures, they

00:51:09.580 --> 00:51:13.870 align:middle line:84%
get both, because you can't
put a fence in the sky

00:51:13.870 --> 00:51:16.180 align:middle line:90%
so that there's a blending.

00:51:16.180 --> 00:51:19.420 align:middle line:84%
Almost think of watercolors
and those two are blending.

00:51:19.420 --> 00:51:21.105 align:middle line:84%
And they're actually
the luckiest.

00:51:21.105 --> 00:51:23.230 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Some of the most
creative, brilliant people

00:51:23.230 --> 00:51:24.580 align:middle line:90%
I know are more on the cusp.

00:51:24.580 --> 00:51:24.990 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: Yes.

00:51:24.990 --> 00:51:25.720 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:51:25.720 --> 00:51:27.386 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: So now
they're actually lucky.

00:51:27.386 --> 00:51:28.240 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Great.

00:51:28.240 --> 00:51:30.916 align:middle line:84%
That really helps in
not being judgmental

00:51:30.916 --> 00:51:33.290 align:middle line:84%
if you really know everyone
has their own unique imprint.

00:51:33.290 --> 00:51:34.810 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: I'm amazed
that people are

00:51:34.810 --> 00:51:37.000 align:middle line:84%
so judgemental in
our society, and I

00:51:37.000 --> 00:51:38.560 align:middle line:90%
don't know when that happened.

00:51:38.560 --> 00:51:41.380 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Because people
are not like them.

00:51:41.380 --> 00:51:45.460 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: Well, since the
dawning of mankind, it's been,

00:51:45.460 --> 00:51:47.650 align:middle line:84%
I guess, irresistible
to make fun

00:51:47.650 --> 00:51:50.080 align:middle line:90%
of what you don't understand.

00:51:50.080 --> 00:51:52.780 align:middle line:84%
I say that to some of the
reporters who review me.

00:51:52.780 --> 00:51:59.790 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHS] You have to take a lot
when you become an astrologer.

00:51:59.790 --> 00:52:03.450 align:middle line:84%
But I always say, just
follow me for six months

00:52:03.450 --> 00:52:05.130 align:middle line:90%
or have your chart done.

00:52:05.130 --> 00:52:09.900 align:middle line:84%
Don't say it doesn't work if
you've not studied it or even

00:52:09.900 --> 00:52:12.160 align:middle line:90%
tried to learn about it.

00:52:12.160 --> 00:52:12.980 align:middle line:90%
Make an attempt.

00:52:12.980 --> 00:52:15.030 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, your
accuracy is incredible.

00:52:15.030 --> 00:52:16.860 align:middle line:84%
And that is, I think,
one of the reasons

00:52:16.860 --> 00:52:18.360 align:middle line:84%
why you have such
a huge following

00:52:18.360 --> 00:52:20.430 align:middle line:90%
is because you are so accurate.

00:52:20.430 --> 00:52:23.500 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: It's the
German side of my family.

00:52:23.500 --> 00:52:25.230 align:middle line:84%
Do you know I wrote
for Vogue Japan,

00:52:25.230 --> 00:52:29.790 align:middle line:84%
and we got this request
from them it was on Excel.

00:52:29.790 --> 00:52:32.640 align:middle line:84%
And they were asking so
many questions about my year

00:52:32.640 --> 00:52:34.539 align:middle line:90%
ahead a few years ago.

00:52:34.539 --> 00:52:37.080 align:middle line:84%
And I said to my secretary, I
don't even know where to begin.

00:52:37.080 --> 00:52:40.230 align:middle line:84%
She said, well,
let's do it together.

00:52:40.230 --> 00:52:44.070 align:middle line:84%
And in my mind, are they
asking me to rewrite this?

00:52:44.070 --> 00:52:46.830 align:middle line:84%
I'm not really sure, but she
said they need it in 10 days,

00:52:46.830 --> 00:52:48.360 align:middle line:90%
so we better start.

00:52:48.360 --> 00:52:51.210 align:middle line:90%
So every night we went through.

00:52:51.210 --> 00:52:54.960 align:middle line:84%
And then I said, tell me if you
want me to rewrite something.

00:52:54.960 --> 00:52:57.840 align:middle line:84%
And they said, Susan, you
just passed a big test.

00:52:57.840 --> 00:52:59.850 align:middle line:90%
We were testing you.

00:52:59.850 --> 00:53:02.760 align:middle line:84%
And we wanted to see if you'd
come up with the right answers.

00:53:02.760 --> 00:53:04.860 align:middle line:84%
And you passed the
test beautifully.

00:53:04.860 --> 00:53:06.520 align:middle line:90%
It was just a test.

00:53:06.520 --> 00:53:08.760 align:middle line:90%
We're not changing your copy.

00:53:08.760 --> 00:53:10.050 align:middle line:90%
Oh my god!

00:53:10.050 --> 00:53:12.720 align:middle line:84%
That is so nice that
you did that, oh my god,

00:53:12.720 --> 00:53:15.630 align:middle line:90%
that you cared enough.

00:53:15.630 --> 00:53:19.310 align:middle line:84%
They kind of cross--checked
in different ways.

00:53:19.310 --> 00:53:20.110 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:53:20.110 --> 00:53:20.870 align:middle line:84%
That's journalistically
responsible.

00:53:20.870 --> 00:53:23.100 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: And I love
that they did that.

00:53:23.100 --> 00:53:23.850 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yeah, you
write for a lot.

00:53:23.850 --> 00:53:24.060 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: Yeah.

00:53:24.060 --> 00:53:25.040 align:middle line:90%
No one else has ever done--

00:53:25.040 --> 00:53:25.320 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:53:25.320 --> 00:53:27.560 align:middle line:84%
"Vogue Japan," "W Korea,"
"Tempo" in Turkey,

00:53:27.560 --> 00:53:29.910 align:middle line:84%
"Claudia Brazil," "Amica
Italy," "Esmo" to Spain, "Vogue

00:53:29.910 --> 00:53:34.000 align:middle line:84%
Germany," "Vogue China," "Grazia
France" and "Elle Australia"

00:53:34.000 --> 00:53:34.954 align:middle line:90%
are just occasionally.

00:53:34.954 --> 00:53:36.120 align:middle line:90%
The others are all the time.

00:53:36.120 --> 00:53:38.010 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So it's
universal language?

00:53:38.010 --> 00:53:39.090 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: Yes.

00:53:39.090 --> 00:53:40.230 align:middle line:90%
And you know what?

00:53:40.230 --> 00:53:45.580 align:middle line:84%
The CEO of the company and the
janitor have the same request.

00:53:45.580 --> 00:53:46.560 align:middle line:90%
They want to find love.

00:53:46.560 --> 00:53:50.560 align:middle line:84%
They want to have their
children do well and be healthy.

00:53:50.560 --> 00:53:53.460 align:middle line:84%
And you want to push back
the borders of your life

00:53:53.460 --> 00:53:58.840 align:middle line:84%
to see what you can
make of your life.

00:53:58.840 --> 00:54:02.940 align:middle line:84%
It's a very creative
experience living.

00:54:02.940 --> 00:54:06.390 align:middle line:84%
And creative people
tend to love astrology.

00:54:06.390 --> 00:54:11.190 align:middle line:84%
They love the symbolism
and the what-ifs

00:54:11.190 --> 00:54:14.940 align:middle line:84%
they can do with astrology,
because astrology has such firm

00:54:14.940 --> 00:54:19.060 align:middle line:84%
structure that, let's say you
came in and say, all right,

00:54:19.060 --> 00:54:21.660 align:middle line:84%
I've just been made editor
in chief of this magazine.

00:54:21.660 --> 00:54:23.700 align:middle line:90%
What should I worry about?

00:54:23.700 --> 00:54:26.280 align:middle line:84%
And just like the
kings in Mesopotamia,

00:54:26.280 --> 00:54:28.110 align:middle line:90%
is there advancing armies?

00:54:28.110 --> 00:54:29.190 align:middle line:90%
Is there famine?

00:54:29.190 --> 00:54:34.860 align:middle line:84%
Are we going to run out of
money for defense, or whatever?

00:54:34.860 --> 00:54:37.980 align:middle line:84%
And I can answer
those questions.

00:54:37.980 --> 00:54:41.820 align:middle line:84%
And I can see your state
of mind when you were five.

00:54:41.820 --> 00:54:44.040 align:middle line:84%
I can say, what happened
when you were really little?

00:54:44.040 --> 00:54:46.620 align:middle line:84%
I said to one of my
photographers, I said,

00:54:46.620 --> 00:54:49.320 align:middle line:84%
what was so sad
when you were born?

00:54:49.320 --> 00:54:51.800 align:middle line:90%
Your mother was just so sad.

00:54:51.800 --> 00:54:53.700 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you see
this in the chart?

00:54:53.700 --> 00:54:56.430 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: And he said, I
don't know, I'm adopted.

00:54:56.430 --> 00:54:58.140 align:middle line:90%
That's what it is.

00:54:58.140 --> 00:55:00.450 align:middle line:90%
She didn't want to give you up.

00:55:00.450 --> 00:55:02.160 align:middle line:90%
Did you ever look for her?

00:55:02.160 --> 00:55:04.080 align:middle line:90%
He said, no, I didn't.

00:55:04.080 --> 00:55:06.570 align:middle line:84%
I was happy with the new
parents they gave me.

00:55:06.570 --> 00:55:08.190 align:middle line:90%
I mean, I was so small.

00:55:08.190 --> 00:55:11.310 align:middle line:84%
I said, it broke her heart
to give you up, David.

00:55:11.310 --> 00:55:13.440 align:middle line:90%
So I can see that in a chart.

00:55:13.440 --> 00:55:15.692 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Is that responsible
to tell someone?

00:55:15.692 --> 00:55:17.400 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: Well, I
think it's nice to know

00:55:17.400 --> 00:55:19.020 align:middle line:90%
that his mother loved him.

00:55:19.020 --> 00:55:19.820 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:55:19.820 --> 00:55:20.820 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:55:20.820 --> 00:55:23.560 align:middle line:90%
That it wasn't, oh, well, here.

00:55:23.560 --> 00:55:24.360 align:middle line:90%
Take my child.

00:55:24.360 --> 00:55:25.402 align:middle line:90%
I don't want him anymore.

00:55:25.402 --> 00:55:26.818 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you can
look at the map

00:55:26.818 --> 00:55:28.710 align:middle line:84%
and see where the
significant events happened

00:55:28.710 --> 00:55:30.940 align:middle line:90%
backwards and forwards.

00:55:30.940 --> 00:55:33.600 align:middle line:84%
So what type of
person comes to you?

00:55:33.600 --> 00:55:35.040 align:middle line:90%
CEOs?

00:55:35.040 --> 00:55:37.200 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: Oh, all
kinds of people.

00:55:37.200 --> 00:55:38.730 align:middle line:84%
Actually, the Four
Seasons asked me

00:55:38.730 --> 00:55:41.500 align:middle line:90%
to do charts for their clients.

00:55:41.500 --> 00:55:44.140 align:middle line:84%
Now, I write so much it's
hard for me to read charts.

00:55:44.140 --> 00:55:46.500 align:middle line:84%
But when the Four
Seasons asks you

00:55:46.500 --> 00:55:50.950 align:middle line:84%
in Los Angeles on Doheny
Drive, I said, OK.

00:55:50.950 --> 00:55:52.020 align:middle line:90%
This one lady came to me.

00:55:52.020 --> 00:55:53.450 align:middle line:90%
She's very quiet.

00:55:53.450 --> 00:55:54.520 align:middle line:90%
I said, what do you do?

00:55:54.520 --> 00:55:56.460 align:middle line:90%
She said, I'm a designer.

00:55:56.460 --> 00:55:58.860 align:middle line:84%
I said, are you here for
the Creative Arts Emmys?

00:55:58.860 --> 00:56:00.390 align:middle line:90%
Because the whole hotel--

00:56:00.390 --> 00:56:01.920 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:56:01.920 --> 00:56:03.330 align:middle line:90%
I said, did you win one?

00:56:03.330 --> 00:56:04.650 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:56:04.650 --> 00:56:05.760 align:middle line:90%
I said, oh, OK.

00:56:05.760 --> 00:56:11.410 align:middle line:84%
Well, I see you finishing a big
project, but it's bittersweet.

00:56:11.410 --> 00:56:13.560 align:middle line:84%
It's right on the
eclipse, July 12th,

00:56:13.560 --> 00:56:16.660 align:middle line:84%
or it was the next
eclipse, July 27th.

00:56:16.660 --> 00:56:18.120 align:middle line:90%
They come two weeks apart.

00:56:18.120 --> 00:56:19.860 align:middle line:90%
She said, it was July 12th.

00:56:19.860 --> 00:56:21.000 align:middle line:90%
I said, what happened?

00:56:21.000 --> 00:56:23.610 align:middle line:84%
She said, it was our
last day of filming,

00:56:23.610 --> 00:56:25.890 align:middle line:84%
and after five years
of being together.

00:56:25.890 --> 00:56:27.660 align:middle line:90%
I said, what do you work on?

00:56:27.660 --> 00:56:32.560 align:middle line:84%
She said, I am the chief
designer for "Game of Thrones."

00:56:32.560 --> 00:56:34.560 align:middle line:84%
And she said we would
never see each other again

00:56:34.560 --> 00:56:36.640 align:middle line:84%
because they've
ended the series.

00:56:36.640 --> 00:56:38.490 align:middle line:90%
So it was bittersweet.

00:56:38.490 --> 00:56:40.770 align:middle line:84%
And I said, but I see you
working on something new.

00:56:40.770 --> 00:56:42.930 align:middle line:84%
But you're in the
library a lot and you're

00:56:42.930 --> 00:56:44.180 align:middle line:90%
doing all this research.

00:56:44.180 --> 00:56:45.420 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you see
all this in a chart?

00:56:45.420 --> 00:56:46.220 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLER: Oh, yeah.

00:56:46.220 --> 00:56:47.680 align:middle line:84%
And I said, it
starts in October.

00:56:47.680 --> 00:56:48.895 align:middle line:90%
So what's happening?

00:56:48.895 --> 00:56:54.240 align:middle line:84%
I said, I'm the first woman
ever to be given the job of set

00:56:54.240 --> 00:56:56.302 align:middle line:90%
designer for "Star Wars."

00:56:56.302 --> 00:56:57.260 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh my goodness.

00:56:57.260 --> 00:57:00.650 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: So I said, you're
going from the past and history

00:57:00.650 --> 00:57:01.620 align:middle line:90%
to the future.

00:57:01.620 --> 00:57:05.090 align:middle line:84%
And people will be studying
your work in the future

00:57:05.090 --> 00:57:07.120 align:middle line:90%
and how you design it.

00:57:07.120 --> 00:57:07.920 align:middle line:90%
Oh my gosh!

00:57:07.920 --> 00:57:09.770 align:middle line:84%
And she said, I know,
it's a big responsibility.

00:57:09.770 --> 00:57:10.820 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's so wonderful.

00:57:10.820 --> 00:57:12.750 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: And I'll be working
in London with Lucasfilm,

00:57:12.750 --> 00:57:13.790 align:middle line:90%
she told me.

00:57:13.790 --> 00:57:15.080 align:middle line:90%
Oh, the best one.

00:57:15.080 --> 00:57:18.741 align:middle line:84%
My assistant said,
it was a couple.

00:57:18.741 --> 00:57:20.990 align:middle line:84%
A gay couple wanted to know,
would you do two of them?

00:57:20.990 --> 00:57:23.360 align:middle line:84%
I said, sure, if they
asked, of course.

00:57:23.360 --> 00:57:25.614 align:middle line:90%
So the girl.

00:57:25.614 --> 00:57:26.780 align:middle line:90%
I said, you've got to write.

00:57:26.780 --> 00:57:29.840 align:middle line:84%
You've got all these
planets and writings.

00:57:29.840 --> 00:57:30.840 align:middle line:90%
It's screaming, write!

00:57:30.840 --> 00:57:31.640 align:middle line:90%
She said, I do.

00:57:31.640 --> 00:57:32.900 align:middle line:90%
I write screenplays.

00:57:32.900 --> 00:57:34.710 align:middle line:90%
But now I'm writing for myself.

00:57:34.710 --> 00:57:39.290 align:middle line:84%
I write for television, but now
I'm writing a movie for myself.

00:57:39.290 --> 00:57:42.950 align:middle line:84%
So now I move to her
partner, who's an Ares,

00:57:42.950 --> 00:57:45.290 align:middle line:84%
and she's got all
these daring planets.

00:57:45.290 --> 00:57:47.210 align:middle line:84%
And I said, you
don't write, but you

00:57:47.210 --> 00:57:49.390 align:middle line:90%
do something, maybe even scary.

00:57:49.390 --> 00:57:50.190 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:57:50.190 --> 00:57:50.990 align:middle line:90%
What do you do?

00:57:50.990 --> 00:57:53.010 align:middle line:84%
She said, I dismantle
bombs for the FBI.

00:57:53.010 --> 00:57:55.230 align:middle line:90%
I'm like, of course you do!

00:57:55.230 --> 00:57:56.030 align:middle line:90%
Oh my god!

00:57:56.030 --> 00:57:59.150 align:middle line:84%
She said, well, right
now I'm on loan for NYPD.

00:57:59.150 --> 00:58:02.690 align:middle line:90%
And I'm like, oh, good.

00:58:02.690 --> 00:58:04.440 align:middle line:84%
Are you two working
together on a movie?

00:58:04.440 --> 00:58:05.240 align:middle line:90%
She said, yeah.

00:58:05.240 --> 00:58:06.380 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Fantastic.

00:58:06.380 --> 00:58:09.110 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: I'm writing a
movie asked on terrorism,

00:58:09.110 --> 00:58:12.470 align:middle line:84%
and Jacqueline is showing
me how to do it properly.

00:58:12.470 --> 00:58:13.820 align:middle line:90%
I said, I love those movies.

00:58:13.820 --> 00:58:15.278 align:middle line:84%
When they're on
the phone, should I

00:58:15.278 --> 00:58:17.780 align:middle line:84%
cut the yellow wire, or the
red wire, or the blue wire?

00:58:17.780 --> 00:58:22.451 align:middle line:84%
And Jacqueline said to me,
what if they're all red?

00:58:22.451 --> 00:58:26.010 align:middle line:84%
I said, oh, gosh,
what happens then?

00:58:26.010 --> 00:58:27.990 align:middle line:84%
She said, I know
how to dismantle it.

00:58:27.990 --> 00:58:28.410 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh my goodness.

00:58:28.410 --> 00:58:30.340 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: I said, your mother
wants you to get a new job.

00:58:30.340 --> 00:58:31.860 align:middle line:90%
She said, yes, but I'm not.

00:58:31.860 --> 00:58:34.320 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS] She was such an Ares.

00:58:34.320 --> 00:58:36.370 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Someone should
do a movie on your life.

00:58:36.370 --> 00:58:38.560 align:middle line:84%
You have had quite
an amazing life.

00:58:38.560 --> 00:58:39.360 align:middle line:90%
I have to ask you--

00:58:39.360 --> 00:58:40.620 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: I love hearing
the stories though.

00:58:40.620 --> 00:58:43.119 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: --what is the biggest
reason why you do what you do?

00:58:43.119 --> 00:58:44.161 align:middle line:90%
What is your biggest why?

00:58:44.161 --> 00:58:45.869 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLER: I want to
do for the world what

00:58:45.869 --> 00:58:46.890 align:middle line:90%
my mother did for me.

00:58:46.890 --> 00:58:49.320 align:middle line:84%
She gave me the courage to
learn how to walk again.

00:58:49.320 --> 00:58:51.570 align:middle line:84%
Believe me, I was getting
so many operations.

00:58:51.570 --> 00:58:53.010 align:middle line:84%
They put you on
a tilt table when

00:58:53.010 --> 00:58:54.960 align:middle line:84%
you have circulatory
problems, just

00:58:54.960 --> 00:58:56.580 align:middle line:90%
to learn how to be upright.

00:58:56.580 --> 00:58:58.500 align:middle line:84%
Then you go on
that parallel bars.

00:58:58.500 --> 00:59:00.250 align:middle line:84%
And just to get a
magazine across the room

00:59:00.250 --> 00:59:01.940 align:middle line:90%
was like going to Arizona.

00:59:01.940 --> 00:59:05.040 align:middle line:84%
And then you're back on the tilt
table after another surgery.

00:59:05.040 --> 00:59:08.220 align:middle line:84%
So you kept feeling
like it's Groundhog Day.

00:59:08.220 --> 00:59:10.110 align:middle line:84%
But my mother, she
would never come in

00:59:10.110 --> 00:59:11.820 align:middle line:90%
and say, how's the pain?

00:59:11.820 --> 00:59:15.600 align:middle line:84%
She'd say, Susie,
when they fix the leg,

00:59:15.600 --> 00:59:18.870 align:middle line:84%
you'll have so many shoes you'll
line them up against the wall

00:59:18.870 --> 00:59:21.330 align:middle line:84%
and say, which shoes
will I wear today?

00:59:21.330 --> 00:59:22.899 align:middle line:90%
And you'll have party dresses.

00:59:22.899 --> 00:59:25.440 align:middle line:84%
You'll be able to go to parties
and you'll be able to travel.

00:59:25.440 --> 00:59:26.940 align:middle line:84%
I could never travel
because I never

00:59:26.940 --> 00:59:28.606 align:middle line:90%
knew when an attack was coming.

00:59:28.606 --> 00:59:29.730 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't even go to camp.

00:59:29.730 --> 00:59:30.850 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't go anywhere.

00:59:30.850 --> 00:59:32.160 align:middle line:90%
I had to be near home.

00:59:32.160 --> 00:59:35.280 align:middle line:84%
She said, the whole world's
going to open up to you.

00:59:35.280 --> 00:59:39.540 align:middle line:10%
And I want to do exactly what my
mother did for me for everybody

00:59:39.540 --> 00:59:43.500 align:middle line:10%
else, because life is hard,
and there are challenges,

00:59:43.500 --> 00:59:46.560 align:middle line:10%
and you need guidelines.

00:59:46.560 --> 00:59:50.220 align:middle line:10%
And my mother said to me, don't
tell anyone you know astrology.

00:59:50.220 --> 00:59:51.637 align:middle line:84%
But it's such an
advantage, Susan.

00:59:51.637 --> 00:59:53.469 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, that's
what you tell everyone,

00:59:53.469 --> 00:59:54.685 align:middle line:90%
so it works for us.

00:59:54.685 --> 00:59:58.170 align:middle line:84%
Well, thank you so much for
sharing with us about destiny

00:59:58.170 --> 00:59:59.370 align:middle line:90%
and about astrology.

00:59:59.370 --> 01:00:00.530 align:middle line:90%
Thank you so much, Susan.

